<title>Stong's Concordance 5850 - 5899</title>
<html><body background="../pic/gray.jpg" bgcolor="c0c0c0" text="000000" link="0000ff" vlink="ff0000" alink=00ff00"> 
<center><a name=Home><br><font size=6>Strong's Concordance Numbers</font></a></center><br>

<center>

</center><p>

<pre>

<br><br><hr><a name=5850><br>5850</a><p>
    <a href="4450.html#4486"<br>4486</a> - "rend asunder", makes pointed reference to the separation
           of the parts
    <a href="2600.html#2608"<br>2608</a> - "to break", denotes the destruction of a things unity or
           completeness
    <a href="2350.html#2352"<br>2352</a> - "to shatter", is suggestive of many fragments and minute
           dispersion


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5851><br>5851</a><p>
    <a href="2350.html#2359"<br>2359</a> - the anatomical or physical term for hair
    <a href="2850.html#2864"<br>2864</a> -  designates the hair as an ornament (notion of length being
            only secondary and suggested) and hence differs from the
            word <a href="2350.html#2359"<br>2359</a> referring to physical hair


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5852><br>5852</a><p>
    <a href="2500.html#2537"<br>2537</a> - denotes the new primarily in reference to quality,
           the fresh, unworn
    <a href="3500.html#3501"<br>3501</a> - denotes the new primarily in reference to time, the young,
           recent


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5853><br>5853</a><p>
    <a href="2500.html#2540"<br>2540</a> - a definitely limited portion of time with the added notion
           of suitableness
    <a href="5550.html#5550"<br>5550</a> - time in general
 


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5854><br>5854</a><p>
    <a href="2700.html#2730"<br>2730</a> - to dwell, settle, temporarily
    <a href="3900.html#3939"<br>3939</a> - to dwell, permanently


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5855><br>5855</a><p>
    <a href="2500.html#2549"<br>2549</a> - denotes a vicious disposition
    <a href="4150.html#4189"<br>4189</a> - denotes the active exercise of a vicious disposition


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5856><br>5856</a><p>
    <a href="2800.html#2812"<br>2812</a> - denotes one who steals by stealth
    <a href="3000.html#3027"<br>3027</a> - denotes one who steals openly


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5857><br>5857</a><p>
    <a href="2900.html#2949"<br>2949</a> - a wave, suggesting uninterrupted successions
    <a href="2800.html#2830"<br>2830</a> - a billow, surge, suggesting size and extension. So to in
           fig. application of the words.


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5858><br>5858</a><p>
    <a href="2750.html#2766"<br>2766</a> - denotes in a strict sense, mixing as combines the
           ingredients into a new compound, chemical mixture
    <a href="3350.html#3396"<br>3396</a> - such a mixture as merely blending or intermingling of them
           promiscuously, as in a mechanical mixture


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5859><br>5859</a><p>
    <a href="2850.html#2851"<br>2851</a> differs from <a href="5050.html#5098"<br>5098</a>  as that which is disciplinary and has
    reference to the him who suffers, while the latter is penal
    and has reference to the satisfaction of him who inflicts it


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5860><br>5860</a><p>
    <a href="4150.html#4192"<br>4192</a> - gives prominence to the effort (work as requiring force)
    <a href="2850.html#2873"<br>2873</a> - refers to the fatigue
    <a href="3400.html#3449"<br>3449</a> - refers to the hardship (chiefly poetic)


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5861><br>5861</a><p>
    <a href="5250.html#5281"<br>5281</a> is the temper which does not easily succumb under
    suffering, <a href="3100.html#3115"<br>3115</a> is the self restraint which does not hastily
    retaliate a wrong.  The one is opposed to cowardice or
    despondency, the other to wrath and revenge.


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5862><br>5862</a><p>
    The distinction often given between these is; <a href="3300.html#3338"<br>3338</a> refers to
    an emotional change, <a href="3300.html#3340"<br>3340</a> to an change of choice, <a href="3300.html#3338"<br>3338</a> has
    reference to particulars, <a href="3300.html#3340"<br>3340</a> to the entire life, <a href="3300.html#3338"<br>3338</a>
    signifies nothing but regret even amounting to remorse, <a href="3300.html#3340"<br>3340</a>
    that reversal of moral purpose known as repentance; does not
    seem to be sustained by usage. But that <a href="3300.html#3340"<br>3340</a> is the fuller
    and nobler term, expressive of moral action and issues, is
    indicated not only by its derivation, but by the greater
    frequency of its use and by the fact it is often used in the
    imperative.


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5863><br>5863</a><p>
    <a href="3300.html#3339"<br>3339</a> - refers to the permanent state to which a change takes place
    <a href="3300.html#3345"<br>3345</a> - refers to the transient condition from which a change happens


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5864><br>5864</a><p>
    <a href="3350.html#3392"<br>3392</a>, "to stain", differs from <a href="3400.html#3435"<br>3435</a>, "to smear", not only in
    its primary and outward sense, but in the circumstance that
    (like Eng.  "stain") it may be used in good part, while <a href="3300.html#3345"<br>3345</a>
    has no worthy reference


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5865><br>5865</a><p>
    <a href="3400.html#3444"<br>3444</a> "form" differs from <a href="4950.html#4976"<br>4976</a> "figure, shape, fashion", as
    that which is intrinsic and essential, from that which is
    outward and accidental. Fritzsche in Php. <a href="0.html#2"<br>2</a>:<a href="0.html#7"<br>7</a> to relate to
    the complete form or nature of a servant; and <a href="4950.html#4976"<br>4976</a> to the
    external form, or human body in <a href="0.html#2"<br>2</a>:<a href="0.html#8"<br>8</a>.


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5866><br>5866</a><p>
    <a href="3500.html#3509"<br>3509</a> is general, <a href="3500.html#3507"<br>3507</a> is specific; the former denotes a great,
    shapeless collection of vapour obscuring the heavens; the latter
    designates particular and definite masses of the same, suggesting
    limit and form.


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5867><br>5867</a><p>
    <a href="3600.html#3624"<br>3624</a> denotes one's household establishment, one's entire property
    <a href="3600.html#3614"<br>3614</a> denotes the dwelling itself


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5868><br>5868</a><p>
    <a href="3800.html#3813"<br>3813</a> - refers exclusively to little children
    <a href="3800.html#3808"<br>3808</a> - refers to a child up to his first school years
    <a href="3800.html#3816"<br>3816</a> - refers to a child of any age
    <a href="3800.html#3814"<br>3814</a> - refers to late childhood and early youth
 
    <a href="3800.html#3816"<br>3816</a>, <a href="5000.html#5043"<br>5043</a> denote a child alike as respects to descent and
    age, reference to the later being more prominent in the
    former word, to descent in <a href="3800.html#3813"<br>3813</a>; but the period <a href="3800.html#3816"<br>3816</a> cover
    is not sharply defined; and, in classic usage as in modern,
    youthful designations cleave to the female sex longer than
    to the male
 
 Compare: <a href="5000.html#5043"<br>5043</a>, <a href="5200.html#5207"<br>5207</a>
 
    <a href="5000.html#5043"<br>5043</a> - gives prominence to physical and outward aspects of
           parentage
    <a href="5200.html#5207"<br>5207</a> - gives prominence to the inward, ethical, legal aspects of
           parentage


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5869><br>5869</a><p>
    <a href="3950.html#3971"<br>3971</a> - denotes descending from father to son
    <a href="3950.html#3967"<br>3967</a> - denotes descending from persons in friendship or feud


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5870><br>5870</a><p>
    <a href="3950.html#3993"<br>3993</a> - one who is so poor he earns his bread by daily labour
    <a href="4400.html#4434"<br>4434</a> - one who only obtains his living by begging


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5871><br>5871</a><p>
    <a href="4150.html#4160"<br>4160</a> - denotes "to do", <a href="4100.html#4138"<br>4138</a> - "to practise"; <a href="4150.html#4160"<br>4160</a> to
    designate performance, <a href="4100.html#4138"<br>4138</a> intended, earnest, habitual,
    performance; <a href="4150.html#4160"<br>4160</a> to denote merely productive action, <a href="4100.html#4138"<br>4138</a>
    definitely directed action; <a href="4150.html#4160"<br>4160</a> to point to the action
    result, <a href="4100.html#4138"<br>4138</a> to the scope and character of the result.


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5872><br>5872</a><p>
    <a href="4650.html#4680"<br>4680</a> - denotes wise, skilled, an expert
    <a href="4900.html#4908"<br>4908</a> - "intelligent", denotes one who can put things together, who
           has insight and comprehension
    <a href="5400.html#5429"<br>5429</a> - "prudent", denotes primarily one who has quick and correct
           perceptions, hence, "discreet, circumspect"


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5873><br>5873</a><p>
    <a href="4800.html#4832"<br>4832</a> - describes what is the essence in character and thus complete
           or durable, not merely a form or outline
    <a href="4950.html#4964"<br>4964</a> - to shape one thing like another and describes what is
           transitory, changeable, and unstable


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5874><br>5874</a><p>
    <a href="5050.html#5083"<br>5083</a> - "to watch or keep"
    <a href="5400.html#5442"<br>5442</a> - "to guard"
 
    <a href="5050.html#5083"<br>5083</a> expresses watchful care and is suggestive of present
    possession, <a href="5400.html#5442"<br>5442</a> indicates safe custody and often implies assault
    from without; <a href="5050.html#5083"<br>5083</a> may mark the result of which <a href="5400.html#5442"<br>5442</a> is the means.


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5875><br>5875</a><p>
    <a href="5100.html#5117"<br>5117</a> - "place", indefinite; a portion of space viewed in reference
           to its occupancy, or as appropriated to itself
    <a href="5550.html#5561"<br>5561</a> - "region, country", extensive; space, yet unbounded
    <a href="5550.html#5564"<br>5564</a> - "parcel of ground", circumscribed; a definite portion of
           space viewed as enclosed or complete in itself


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5876><br>5876</a><p>
    <a href="5600.html#5603"<br>5603</a> is the generic term; <a href="5550.html#5568"<br>5568</a> and <a href="5200.html#5215"<br>5215</a> are specific, the
    former designating a song which took its general character
    from the OT Psalms, although not restricted to them, the
    later a song of praise.  While the leading idea of <a href="5550.html#5568"<br>5568</a> is a
    musical accompaniment, and that of <a href="5200.html#5215"<br>5215</a> praise to God, <a href="5600.html#5603"<br>5603</a>
    is the general word for a song, whether accompanied or not,
    whether of praise  or on any other subject. Thus it is quite
    possible for the same song to be at once described by all
    three of these words.


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5877><br>5877</a><p>
    The words overlap and distinctions often disappear; yet the
    suggestion of a welcoming or appropriating reception
    generally cleaves to <a href="1200.html#1209"<br>1209</a>.


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5878><br>5878</a><p>
 Synonyms


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5880><br>5880</a><p>
 Synonyms


<a href="#home"><img src="../pic/top.jpg" border=0></a>&nbsp&nbsp<a href="../index.html"><img src="../pic/hom.jpg" border=0></a>
<br><br><hr><a name=5882><br>5882</a><p>
