<br><br><hr><a name=649><br>649</a><p> apostello {ap-os-tel'-lo}
from <a href="550.html#575"<br>575</a> and <a href="4700.html#4724"<br>4724</a>; TDNT - 1:398,67; v

 AV - send 110, send forth 15, send away 4, send out 2, misc 2; 133

 1) to order (one) to go to a place appointed
 2) to send away, dismiss
    2a) to allow one to depart, that he may be in a state of
        liberty
    2b) to order one to depart, send off
    2c) to drive away

 For Synonyms see entry 5813


