<html>
<head>
   <title>Other Issues</title>
   <meta name="Author" content="Jonathan W. Pait">
   <meta name="GENERATOR" content="Mozilla/2.0GoldB1 (Win32)">
</head>
<body text="#000000" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#0000EE" vlink="#551A8B" alink="#FF0000">

<div align=center><p><b><i><font SIZE=+3>Other Issues</font></i></b>&nbsp;

<br>
<hr   width="100%"></p></div>

<p>
<br><img src="hurt.gif" hspace=10 vspace=5 border=0  height=196 width =152 align=left ><b><font COLOR="#FF0000"><font SIZE=+2>What
to Do When It Hurts 
<br></font></font></b><font COLOR="#000000"><font SIZE=+1>There's no doubt
about it. &nbsp;People will hurt you when you open up to minister to them.
&nbsp;Here's help in knowing how to handle the hurt. 
<br>
<br></font></font><b><font COLOR="#0000FF"><font SIZE=+2>When AIDS&nbsp;Comes
Home 
<br></font></font></b><font COLOR="#000000"><font SIZE=+1>AIDS/HIV may
take ten or more years to destroy a life.&nbsp;&nbsp;This Christian family
is dealing with the infection times three.&nbsp;&nbsp;The principles presented
can apply to any long-term disease situation. 
<br>
<br></font></font><b><font COLOR="#808000"><font SIZE=+2>Attitude Adjustments

<br></font></font></b><font SIZE=+1>Are you what you say you are?&nbsp;&nbsp;Or,
are you playing a role--going through the motion without the proper emotion?&nbsp;&nbsp;If
so, then you need an attitude adjustment.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you are right on
the inside, then you'll be right on the outside; however, there are a lot
of preachers who play the hypocrite. 
<br>
<br></font><b><font COLOR="#FF00FF"><font SIZE=+2>Help! &nbsp;I'm a Preacher's
Kid! 
<br></font></font></b><font SIZE=+1>Your greatest ministry starts at home.&nbsp;&nbsp;Consider
carefully the opportunity God has given you to affect this world through
raising Godly children.</font> 
<br>
<br>
<hr   width="100%"></p>

<p><i><font SIZE=+2>We trust that this sample of topics that are discussed
in Today's Christian Preacher will show you the wealth of encouragement
that awaits you when you subscribe.&nbsp;&nbsp;Some other topics include:</font></i></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+3>WHAT IS THE STATE OF YOUR UNION? 
<br></font></b><font SIZE=+2>Did you know that the quality of your relationship
with your wife can greatly affect God's blessing on your ministry?&nbsp;&nbsp;Here
are important steps you can take to make your marriage all it can be to
the glory of God. 
<br>
<br></font><b><font SIZE=+3>CHRISTIAN PREACHERS AND THE MODERN-DAY GNOSTICS

<br></font></b><font SIZE=+2>Watch out, Preacher!&nbsp;&nbsp;As you fight
against wickedness and sin in your church and your community, there is
a silent stalker on your trail.&nbsp;&nbsp;Quietly but definitely, it's
trying to shorten--and maybe even end--your ministry! 
<br>
<br></font><b><font SIZE=+3>MAKING TIME FOR YOUR CHILDREN 
<br></font></b><font SIZE=+2>Do you spend enough time with your children?&nbsp;&nbsp;Are
you building a relationship with them that will make them want to serve
the Lord?&nbsp;&nbsp;Or will they despise the ministry that keeps you away
from them?&nbsp;&nbsp;Here are some great thoughts on this vital subject.

<br>
<br></font><b><font SIZE=+3>FINDING THE COMFORT OF CHRIST WHEN YOU HURT

<br></font></b><font SIZE=+2>Trouble comes into our lives.&nbsp;&nbsp;How
we respond to it determines whether it will have a good or bad effect in
our lives.&nbsp;&nbsp;See why trusting God to be with us in every storm
is a learned reaction.</font> 
<br>
<br>
<hr  width="100%"></p>

<p>
<br>
<br><img src="love.gif" hspace=10 vspace=5 border=0  height=196 width =152 align=right ><b><font COLOR="#0000A0"><font SIZE=+2>Avoiding
&quot;The Fall&quot; of Adultery 
<br></font></font></b>One survey revealed that almost 20% of pastors had
engaged in some form of inappropriate sexual contact with someone other
that their spouse.&nbsp;&nbsp;What are you doing to avoid &quot;The Fall?&quot;

<br>
<br><b><font COLOR="#FF80C0"><font SIZE=+2>Principles of Personal Self
Discipline 
<br></font></font></b>Without a doubt this is the age of indulgence and
indiscipline.&nbsp;&nbsp;Adam's race seems to be constitutionally incapable
of saying &quot;no&quot; to itself.&nbsp;&nbsp;How about you?&nbsp;&nbsp;Are
you decidedly disciplined or definitely defeated in the effort?&nbsp;&nbsp;Here
is Biblical help. 
<br>
<br><b><font COLOR="#FF8000"><font SIZE=+2>Rules Without Relationships
= Rebellion 
<br></font></font></b>Regulations established within the structure of relationships
result in security, character, and Christlikeness.&nbsp;&nbsp;Rules without
relationship equal rebellion.&nbsp;&nbsp;How are you doing in this critical
area? 
<br>
<br><b><font COLOR="#400040"><font SIZE=+2>A Biblical View of Entertainment

<br></font></font></b>Today's entertainment industry beckons to you and
your family.&nbsp;&nbsp;Developing a set of Biblical standards by which
to determine what entertainment you and your family will enjoy requires
wisdom.&nbsp;&nbsp;Here are the questions to ask yourself. 
<br>
<br>
