<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Inspiration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<center><H3>I believe in<BR>
the inspiration of the Bible<BR>
(both the Old and the New Testaments)</H3>
</center>
<img src="/graphics/horiz.gif">

<DL>
<DT><P><B>The Bible is God-breathed.</B>

<DD><P><I>For the prophecy came not in old time by the will of man: but
holy men of God spake [as they were] moved by the Holy Ghost.
</I> <a href="/bible/2p/1.html#21">(2 Peter 1:21)</a>
<DT><HR><B>Inspiration is plenary (including all the Scripture) and
verbal (extending to the words of Scripture).  The Bible does not
merely <I>contain</I> the Word of God; it <I>is</I> the Word of God.</B>

<DD><P><I>All scripture [is] given by inspiration of God, and [is]
profitable for doctrine, for reproof, for correction, for
instruction in righteousness.</I> <a href="/bible/2tm/3.html#16">(2 Timothy 3:16)</a>

<DT><HR><B>The Bible will never change.</B>

<DD><P><I>For ever, O LORD, thy word is settled in heaven.
</I> (Psalm 119:89)

<DT><HR><B>Not everything in the Bible is true; that is, God's Word
records the lies of evil beings.  But when God speaks, the Word
is true.</B>

<DD><P><I>And the serpent said unto the woman, Ye shall not surely die.
</I> (Genesis 3:4)

<P><I>In hope of eternal life, which God, that cannot lie, promised
before the world began.</I> <a href="/bible/ti/1.html#2">(Titus 1:2)</a>

<DT><HR><B>Not everything in the Bible is <I>literally</I> true; that is, God's Word
often uses figures of speech.</B>

<DD><P><I>For ye shall go out with joy, and be led forth with peace: the
mountains and the hills shall break forth before you into
singing, and all the trees of the field shall clap [their] hands.
</I> (Isaiah 55:12)

<DT><HR><B>The godly person delights in the Word of God.</B>

<DD><P><I>But his delight [is] in the law of the LORD; and in his law doth
he meditate day and night.</I> (Psalm 1:2)

<P><I>Thy words were found, and I did eat them; and thy word was unto
me the joy and rejoicing of mine heart: for I am called by thy
name, O LORD God of hosts.</I> (Jeremiah 15:16)
</DL>

<HR>
