<h5>
<hr  width="100%">
<br><img src="tcplrg.gif" alt="Sample Issue Cover" hspace=10 vspace=5 border=0  height=522 width =400 align=left >&nbsp;

<br><b><i><font COLOR="#0000FF"><font SIZE=+2>Prayer, Fasting, and Spiritual
Renewal
<br>A</font></font></i></b><font COLOR="#000000"><font SIZE=+0>re your
prayers wasted? &nbsp;Do you pray hedonistically? &nbsp;Do you desicre
to see progress in the sanctification of the inner man? &nbsp;Here are
some things to think about.
<br>
<br></font></font><b><i><font COLOR="#FF0000"><font SIZE=+2>Materialism
and the Man of God
<br>M</font></font></i></b><font COLOR="#000000"><font SIZE=+0>aterialism
has been defined as the practice of attaching too much importance and value
to material things. It is certainly not new. &nbsp;However, the man of
God needs to have a right perspective on all the &quot;stuff&quot; of life.

<br>
<br></font></font><b><i><font COLOR="#FF00FF"><font SIZE=+2>When Is It
Time to Leave
<br>T</font></font></i></b><font COLOR="#000000"><font SIZE=+0>his pastor
changed ministries after 24 years of service. &nbsp;Here are eight things
to consider if you are thinking about moving on.
<br>
<br></font></font><b><i><font COLOR="#808000"><font SIZE=+2>Getting Along
with Difficult People
<br>A</font></font></i></b><font COLOR="#000000"><font SIZE=+0>re you a
'regular' or 'irregular' person? &nbsp;No, we're not talking about clothing.
&nbsp;How do you get along with the 'weird sheep' God sends your way?</font></font><a href="story2.html"><img src="read.gif" border=0 align=top></a>
<br>
