<h5>
<hr width="100%">
<br><img src="tctlrg.gif" alt="Cover of Spring Issue." hspace=10 vspace=5 border=0  height=509 width =400 align=left >&nbsp;

<br><b><i><font COLOR="#0000FF"><font SIZE=+2>Why Christians Should Go
to a Christian College
<br>S</font></font></i></b>ecular university or Christian college. &nbsp; Which
is best for the Christian student? &nbsp;Many say, &quot;I've been brought
up in a Christian home. &nbsp;I've attended Christian schools or been in
church all my life. &nbsp;I'm ready to face the real world now.&quot;&nbsp;&nbsp;But
are you really ready for what secular schools present? &nbsp;Choose carefully.
&nbsp;It's your life!
<br>
<br><b><i><font COLOR="#FF0000"><font SIZE=+2>Why Is Life So Unfair?
<br>I</font></font></i></b>f we're honest with ourselves, there's probably
not one of us who has not sometime been frustrated by God's apparent lack
of fairness. &nbsp;It can be pretty scary when we start to think that God may
be less than fair. &nbsp;Should we expect things to be fair in this life? &nbsp;Here
are some things to think about if your've ever said or thought, &nbsp;&quot;That's
not fair.&quot;
<br>
<br><b><i><font COLOR="#FF00FF"><font SIZE=+2>Good and Bad Influences
<br>O</font></font></i></b>ur friends will have an effect upon how we think,
that attitudes we develop, and the activities we get involved in. &nbsp;While
we can be (and should be) friendly with everyone, it is wise to be very
selective when we are establishing close friendships. &nbsp;Here are guidelines
to help.
<br>
<br><b><i><font COLOR="#008040"><font SIZE=+2>When AIDS Came to My House

<br>H</font></font></i></b>ow would you feel if your parents told you that
they both AND your little sister were infected wtih HIV and probably would
die from AIDS? &nbsp;This young man has lived with the ultimate nightmare in
his home. &nbsp;Benefit from his insights. <i><a HREF="story.html"><IMG SRC="read.gif" border=0 align=top></a></i>
