<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H1>Admission to the School of Applied Studies
</H1>
<CENTER><CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/horiz.gif"></CENTER><BR><BR></CENTER><BR>
The School of Applied Studies is designed to meet the educational needs of individuals of mature experience and/or irregular academic background who are not interested in earning a baccalaureate degree. All candidates for admission to the School of Applied Studies must give satisfactory evidence of good character. Though the work will be conducted on a post high school level, graduation from high school is not a requirement for admission; but all individuals making application must be entitled to honorable dismissal from each of the institutions that they have previously attended and must be at least 18 years of age.
<BR><BR>
