<h2><IMG SRC="greendot.gif" Height=14 Width=15 ALT=" ">
<FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">
What&#0146;s New in western Missouri and eastern Kansas:
</font></h2>

<UL COMPACT TYPE=square>
<li>We&#0146;ve updated
<em><a href="dmevents.htm">Diabetes Events in western Missouri, in eastern Kansas, and in Cyberspace:</a></em>
<ul>
<li>The dates for the
ADA Metropolitan Patient Education meetings have been added.
<nobr>[Feb 10]</nobr>

</ul>
<li><em><a href="jdf-kcc.htm">The Kansas City Chapter of the JDF</a></em> updates us on their activities
<nobr>[Feb 09]</nobr>
</ul>

<h2><IMG SRC="greendot.gif" Height=14 Width=15 ALT=" ">
<FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">
Not quite new, but worth mentioning:
</font></h2>

<UL COMPACT TYPE=square>

<li>Several of our webpages have a two-column format; alternate webpages (with the same content)
that are arranged in the traditional full-page width are now (usually!) available.

<li>We list our choices of <em><a href="fourstar.htm">Four-Star Diabetes Websites</a></em>
<nobr>[Jan 27]</nobr>
<li><em><a href="http://www.acponline.org">The American College of Physicians</a></em> has published
an article on <em><a href="http://www.acponline.org/journals/news/dec96/cybrquak.htm">cyberquakery</a></em> that should be read by everyone interested in using the
Internet for healthcare information.
<nobr>[Jan 11]</nobr>

<li>This website (and other diabetes websites) have been inundated recently
with requests to link to websites that have no educational content, and are nothing but advertising (to buy a book or videotape or whatever).
<strong>We will not link to what we consider to be webadvertisements, unless the promoters of
these websites are willing to let us indicate that the hyperlink
is to an advertisement, and are paying an appropriate fee to us for the publicity.
</strong> (We would greatly appreciate any grants, advertising revenues, donations, or other tokens of support of our efforts, but will retain the
perogative of what advertising to accept or reject. Any advertisements at 
<strong><font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">D</font><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">M</font><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font></STRONG>
will clearly indicate that they are &#0147;Paid Advertising.&#0148;)
<nobr>[Jan 11]</nobr>

<li>We are continuing to reinvent the appearance of the
<strong><font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">D</font><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">M</font><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font></STRONG>.

Watch for more pages with the blue vertical band on the left during the next few weeks.

<li>Our <em><a href="sitemap.htm">Site Map</a></em> now includes the complete URL of every webpage.
Accordingly, we invite you to download the
<nobr><em><a href="sitemap.htm">Site Map</a></em></nobr> webpage, and look it over anytime.
Then, it&#0146;s simply a matter of clicking on any hyperlink on
your copy of the Site Map, and you&#0146;ll
be able to hyperlink back to the &#0147;live&#0148; version of the
<nobr><strong><font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">D</font><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">M</font><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR .</font></STRONG></nobr>
<nobr>[Updated Feb 15]</nobr>

<li>The <STRONG>
<font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">D</font><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">M</font><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font></STRONG>
now has an
<nobr>
<em><a href="dm-index.htm">index.</a></em></nobr>
If you are searching for a word or concept at this website,
and wish it were in the index, please <em><A HREF="mailto:monitor@mdcc.com">
send an e-mail</a></em> and we&#0146;ll put the word into the index!
<nobr>[Updated Feb 15]</nobr>

<li><nobr>
<em><a href="bragging.htm">We&#0146;re bragging</a></em></nobr> about the
<STRONG>
<font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">D</font><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">M</font><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font></STRONG>
<nobr>[Dec 26]</nobr>

<li>
We have a separate page for
<a href="techie.htm"><em>Technical Data about the Website</em></a> <nobr>[Dec 28]</nobr>

<li>
You can review
<EM><A HREF="prev-wks.htm">
<strong>P</strong>revious <strong>W</strong>hat&#0146;s <strong>N</strong>ew <strong>L</strong>ists</A></EM>
at the
<STRONG>
<font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">D</font><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">M</font><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font></STRONG>
<nobr>[Feb 01]</nobr>
</ul>
