<title>Diabetes Monitor - Four Star Sites</TITLE></HEAD>
<body BGCOLOR="#DFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" ALINK="#0000FF" background="bd2.gif" VLINK="#FF0000">
<a name="top"></a><a name="_top"></a>
<table>
<td>
<IMG src="spinstar.gif" height=47 width=47 ALT=" " align=left>
</td><td>
<h2><strong>
<font SIZE="+3"><A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font>
<br>
<FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">
Four-Star Diabetes Websites</FONT>
</td><br>
</table>
</h2></strong>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" width=100% Height=2 ALT=" ">
<blockquote><P>
<blockquote><P><font color="#ff00cc">
 . . . as of January 27, 1997
</font></blockquote><P>

<center><p>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
<blockquote><P>
<h3>These sites have been selected by a panel of webmasters 
of diabetes websites
as representing the
<nobr>highest quality</nobr>
<nobr>diabetes websites.</nobr>
<P>
Listed alphabetically.
</h3>
</blockquote>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
</center>
<!-- beginning of listings -->

<P>
<IMG SRC="fourstar.gif" ALT=" Four Stars " height=22 width=88>
<em><a href="http://www.noah.cuny.edu/diabetes/diabetes.html">Ask NOAH About: Diabetes</a></em>
 is a part of New York Online Access to Health (NOAH). In both English and Spanish.
(<em><A HREF="mailto:mendosa@cruzio.com">RM</A></em>)

<P>
<IMG SRC="fourstar.gif" ALT=" Four Stars " height=22 width=88>
<EM><A HREF="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/index.html">
Children with Diabetes</a></EM>
Tons of information for children
with insulin-dependent diabetes and their parents,
and for everyone interested in learning more.
(<em><A HREF="mailto:mendosa@cruzio.com">RM</A></em>,
<em><A HREF="mailto:wwq@mdcc.com">WQ</A></em>)

<P>
<IMG SRC="fourstar.gif" ALT=" Four Stars " height=22 width=88>
<em><A HREF="http://www.diabetes.com/">Diabetes.com</A></em>
is a comprehensive Web resource
published by Matthew Naythons, M.D., and the staff of NetHealth, publisher
of the Internet Health, Fitness, and Medicine Yellow Pages (Osborne McGraw
Hill). NetHealth is a division of Epicenter Communications Inc.
(<em><A HREF="mailto:mendosa@cruzio.com">RM</A></em>)

<P>
<IMG SRC="fourstar.gif" ALT=" Four Stars " height=22 width=88>
<em><a href="http://www.mediconsult.com/diabetes/">Diabetes Information for the Well Informed</a></em>
is a comprehensive 
source of information and services dedicated to patients and their relatives.
One of its missions is to provide free, easy to understand, accurate
and up to date information about diabetes.
(<em><A HREF="mailto:mendosa@cruzio.com">RM</A></em>)

<P>
<IMG SRC="fourstar.gif" ALT=" Four Stars " height=22 width=88>
<em><a href="index.htm">Diabetes Monitor</a></em>
One of the most valuable Web sites for diabetics, the Diabetes Monitor
is also one of the most comprehensive and best designed.
<em><A HREF="mailto:mendosa@cruzio.com">&#0151;RM</A></em>
(<em><A HREF="mailto:mendosa@cruzio.com">RM</A></em>,
<em><A HREF="mailto:raprice@m3.interserv.com">RP</A></em>)

<P>
<IMG SRC="fourstar.gif" ALT=" Four Stars " height=22 width=88>
<EM><a href="http://home.sprynet.com/interserv/raprice/diabetes.htm">
Feline Diabetes Web Site</a></em>
&#0147;This site is maintained by a HUMAN physician who is the owner of a diabetic cat. Input is welcome (and needed!) from all
other cat owners and interested people who would like to see a comprehensive information center for helping feline diabetics.&#0148;
(<em><A HREF="mailto:wwq@mdcc.com">WQ</A></em>)
<P>
<IMG SRC="fourstar.gif" ALT=" Four Stars " height=22 width=88>
<em><a href="http://www.lilly.com/diabetes">Managing Your Diabetes</a></em>
Diabetes information for health care professionals, patients, and consumers in the
US... From Eli Lilly and Company
(<em><A HREF="mailto:raprice@m3.interserv.com">RP</A></em>)

<P>
<IMG SRC="fourstar.gif" ALT=" Four Stars " height=22 width=88>
<em><a href="http://dnet.ori.org/newuser/">
Oregon Research Institute Diabetes Network Pilot Project</a></em> 
is a site of the Computer Mediated Support for Diabetes
Self-Management project at Oregon Research Institute. You will find a host of resources available on D-Net to assist 
and support you in your diabetes self-care efforts. Some of the features you will find are diabetes specific 
information, nutrition, exercise and healthy eating tips, diabetes support groups, a live chat area, and individualized 
personal self care planning.
(<em><A HREF="mailto:mendosa@cruzio.com">RM</A></em>)

<P>
<IMG SRC="fourstar.gif" ALT=" Four Stars " height=22 width=88>
<em><a href="http://www.niddk.nih.gov/NIDDK_HomePage.html">The National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Disease</a></em>
</FONT> of the National Institutes of
Health (NIH) in Bethesda, Maryland, had patient information documents on diabetes and its complications
and news releases. The documents include &quot;Diabetes Control and Complications Trial&quot; and
&quot;Diabetes Dictionary.&quot; 
(<em><A HREF="mailto:mendosa@cruzio.com">RM</A></em>)

