<FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">
Thyroid Information<br>on the Internet
</FONT>
</td><br>
</table>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" width=100% Height=2 ALT=" ">
</h2></strong>
<blockquote><P>


<blockquote><P><font color="#ff00cc">
 . . . as of February 2, 1997
</font></blockquote><P>


<center><p>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
</center>
<blockquote><P><blockquote><P><center><h3>
Thyroid disorders frequently coexist with diabetes. Here are some hyperlinks to thyroid
information on the internet.
</h3>
</blockquote></blockquote>
<p>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
</center>

<blockquote><P>
<IMG SRC="cwd_1414.gif" alt=" " height=14 width=14>
<em><a href="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/d_0d_0lc.htm#Thyroid">
Thyroid Questions and Answers</a></em>
(&quot;http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/d_0d_0lc.htm#Thyroid&quot;)

At <em><A HREF="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/index.html">children with
DIABETES</A></em>

<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://www.clark.net/pub/tfa/">
Thyroid Foundation of America</a></em>
(&quot;http://www.clark.net/pub/tfa/&quot;)


<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://medhlp.netusa.net/general/THYROID.TXT">Hypothyroidism
and Hyperthyroidism</a></em>
(&quot;http://medhlp.netusa.net/general/THYROID.TXT
&quot;)


<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://cpmcnet.columbia.edu/health.sci/.gcps/gcps022.html">Screening
for Thyroid Disease</a> </em>
(&quot;http://cpmcnet.columbia.edu/health.sci/.gcps/gcps022.html
&quot;)
From the Columbia University Health Sciences Division
of Columbia Presbyterian Medical Center

<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://www.icsi.net/medical/chest/med50715.txt">Thyroid Disease</a>
</em>
(&quot;http://www.icsi.net/medical/chest/med50715.txt&quot;)

By Philip Suarez, M.D.

<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://www.io.org/~thyroid/Canada.html">Thyroid Foundation
of Canada</a> </em>
(&quot;http://www.io.org/~thyroid/Canada.html&quot;)

<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://www-med.stanford.edu/MedCenter/Communications/Stanmed/Summer95/thyroid.html">Unmasking
Thyroid Disease</a> </em>
&#0147;With symptoms that masquerade as myriad medical and mental disorders, thyroid disease often eludes
diagnosis.&#0148;
(&quot;http://www-med.stanford.edu/MedCenter/Communications/Stanmed/Summer95/thyroid.html&quot;)
By Alana Mikkelsen
at Stanford Medical Center

<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://endrcr06.mda.uth.tmc.edu/Sherman/Thyroidectomy/thyroid.htm">Patient Information Thyroid Surgery Pamphlet</a> </em>
(&quot;http://endrcr06.mda.uth.tmc.edu/Sherman/Thyroidectomy/thyroid.htm&quot;)
The University of Texas M. D. Anderson Cancer Center


<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="news:alt.support.thyroid">Thyroid Support USENET Newsgroup</a> </em>
(&quot;news:alt.support.thyroid&quot;)


<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://endrcr06.mda.uth.tmc.edu/gagel/mtc.html">Familial Medullary Thyroid Carcinoma:  A Guide for Affected Families</a></em>
(&quot;http://endrcr06.mda.uth.tmc.edu/gagel/mtc.html&quot;)

By Robert F. Gagel, M.D.,
University of Texas M.D. Anderson Cancer Center,
Houston, Texas
and Zoila Torres Feldman, R.N., M.S.,
Great Brook Valley Health Center,
Worcester, Massachusetts
<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://www.thyroid.org">American Thyroid Association</a></em>
(&quot;http://www.thyroid.org&quot;)

<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://www.icb2.usp.br/~acbianco/"> The Latin American Thyroid Society</a></em>
(&quot;http://www.icb2.usp.br/~acbianco/&quot;)
From Sao Paulo, Brazil

</blockquote>

