</td><td>
<h2><strong>
<font SIZE="+3"><A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font>
<br>
<FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">
On-line Resources for Diabetics
</FONT>
</td><br>
</table>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" width=100% Height=2 ALT=" ">
</h2></strong>
<center>
<h2>Organizations and Charities Web Sites</h2><br>
<h3><b>By Rick Mendosa</b>
<br>(Used with Permission)</h3>
<p>
Most Recent Update: February 10, 1997
</center>
<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center SIZE=2 NOSHADE>
<blockquote><blockquote>
<p>
<A HREF ="t.gif"></a><img src="t.gif" align=left alt=T>his Web page brings 
together in one place descriptions of and links to only those Web pages of organizations and 
charities dealing with diabetes, 
but is linked to the seven other On-line Resources for Diabetes pages dealing with other Web pages,
other parts of the Internet, and other on-line services. Those links that I think are especially valuable are marked 
in <FONT COLOR="Red">red.</FONT>
<p>
<ol>
<p>
<li>The Texas Affiliate of the American Diabetes Association maintains the Diabetes Texas WWW Site. 
Its URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.versa.com/ada/">http://www.versa.com/ada/</a>
<p>
<li>The American Diabetes Association (ADA)has a Web site that includes a complete list of affiliates. It 
also features a new healthy recipe every day. Its URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.diabetes.org/default.asp">http://www.diabetes.org/default.asp</a><br>
<p>
For the ADA's &quot;Clinical Practice Recommendations 1997&quot; see<br>
<a href="http://www.diabetes.org/DiabetesCare/Supplement197/default.htm">http://www.diabetes.org/DiabetesCare/Supplement197/default.htm</a>
<p>
<li></i>The Kansas City Chapter of the Juvenile Diabetes Foundation has a home
page including a schedule of upcoming events. Its URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.mdcc.com/jdf-kcc.htm">http://www.mdcc.com/jdf-kcc.htm</a>
<p>
<li>The Oregon Diabetes Resource InfoBase is intended to be a clearing house for diabetes
 resources, assistance, information, and events of importance for all individuals within the diabetes community 
in Oregon and Southwest Washington state. It is presented by the American Diabetes Association/Oregon 
Affiliate. The URL is <br>
<a href="http://www.teleport.com/~diabetes/">http://www.teleport.com/~diabetes/</a>
It has a mirror site at<br>
<a href="http://www.findcure.org/~diabetes/">http://www.findcure.org/~diabetes/</a>
<p>
<li>The web site of the Canadian Diabetes Association promotes the health of Canadians through
    diabetes research, education, service, and advocacy. Its URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.diabetes.ca/">http://www.diabetes.ca/</a>
<p>
<li>Diabetic Educators of Eastern Massachusetts (DEEM) is a chapter of the American Association
of Diabetes Educators.  DEEM's URL is <br>
<a href="http://www.ultranet.com/~kmaurer/deem/index.htm">http://www.ultranet.com/~kmaurer/deem/index.htm</a>
<p>
<li>The Diabetes Youth Foundation of Indiana is a not-for-profit group whose mission is to
improve the lives of children with diabetes and their families. Its URL is<br>
<a href="http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/Sam_Flanders/">http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/Sam_Flanders/</a>
<p>
<li>The Juvenile Diabetes Foundation is a not-for-profit, voluntary health agency whose
 mission is to support and fund research to find a cure for diabetes and its complications.
 JDF gives more money directly to diabetes research than any other private health agency
          in the world, according to its Web site at:<br>
<a href="http://www.jdfcure.com/">http://www.jdfcure.com/</a>
<p>
<li>The Diabetics Division of the National Federation of the Blind is a support and 
information network for all diabetics, especially those who are blind or losing vision. Its URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.nfb.org/diabetes.htm">http://www.nfb.org/diabetes.htm</a>
<p>
<li>The Latin American Diabetes Association -- Asociacion Latinoamericana de 
Diabetes (ALAD) -- has a Spanish-language home page maintained by 
<a href="mailto:IML1@vms.cis.pitt.edu">Ingrid M. Libman de Gordon.</a> 
Its URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.pitt.edu/~iml1/diabetes/ALAD.html">http://www.pitt.edu/~iml1/diabetes/ALAD.html</a>
<p>
<li> Dr. Libman also has a &quot;Diabetes Home Page&quot; in Spanish. The URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.pitt.edu/~iml1/diabetes/generalspa.html">http://www.pitt.edu/~iml1/diabetes/generalspa.html</a>
<p>
<li>Under the direction of medical director <a href="mailto:rcreech@gnn.com">Dr. Robert Creech,</a> CURE Diabetes Inc. in 
Hermitage, Tennessee, is a non-profit organization dedicated to helping people live well with diabetes. Toward 
this end, Diabetes Wellness Camp is held as an annual event, this year at Camp Easter Seal. It is a week long, 
overnight camp for children, and young adults with diabetes (siblings/friends) are also welcome. Right now the camp 
is looking hard for a dietician. The URL is<br>
<a href="http://members.gnn.com/rcreech/index.htm">http://members.gnn.com/rcreech/index.htm</a>
<p>
<li>The International Diabetic Athletes Association headquartered in Phoenix, Arizona, provides education for diabetics
regarding the benefits and risks of exercise. Its URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.getnet.com/~idaa/">http://www.getnet.com/~idaa/</a>
<p>
<li>AADEnet is the official site of the American Association of Diabetes Educators. It represents more than 10,000 
healthcare professionals who provide diabetes education and care. Its URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.AADEnet.org/">http://www.AADEnet.org/</a>
<p>
<li> Diabetes Australia -Tasmania Inc. is a registered charity and community based support organization, which 
through a comprehensive health service has worked for all people with diabetes and their families since 1955. Its 
URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.tased.edu.au/tasonline/diabetes/diabetes.htm">http://www.tased.edu.au/tasonline/diabetes/diabetes.htm</a>
<p>
<li> AACE On-Line is the Web site of the American Association of Clinical Endocrinologists. Here you can 
find the AACE's guidelines for the management of diabetes. The URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.aace.com/">http://www.aace.com/</a>
<p>
<li>The Islet Foundation in Toronto, Ontario, Canada (TIF) was formed exclusively for the purpose of funding 
human trials of what appears to be a promising cure for diabetes, namely the transplantation of microencapsulated 
pig islets without the use of toxic immunosuppressive drugs.  In the September 15, 1996, issue of <i>The Journal 
of Clinical Investigation</i>, which is linked at this site, Dr. Tony Sun at University of Toronto reported success 
curing diabetes in monkeys through this method, without adverse effects. The URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.islet.org/index1.htm">http://www.islet.org/index1.htm</a>
<p>
<li> The Diabetic Educational Center was founded to help people with diabetes in Nevada find local 
resources and information. The URL is <br>
<a href="http://server2.powernet.net/~interface/dec/">http://server2.powernet.net/~interface/dec/</a>
<p>
<li> Diabetes Australia-New South Wales is the third diabetes Web site from Australia. The URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.talent.com.au/diabetes/diabeteswelcome">http://www.talent.com.au/diabetes/diabeteswelcome</a>
<p>
<li> Insulin Dependent Diabetes Trust (IDDT) is a charity registered in the United Kingdom. Here is a lot of
information and a powerful site search engine. The URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.traders.co.uk/insulintrust/">http://www.traders.co.uk/insulintrust/</a>
<p>
<li> The California affiliate of the American Diabetes Association now has an extensive Web page. 
The URL is <br>
<a href="http://www.diabetes.org/adaca/">http://www.diabetes.org/adaca/
</a>
<p>
<li> The Human Biological Data Interchange (HBDI) in Philadelphia, a program of the National 
Disease Research Interchange, was founded in 1988 in partnership with the Juvenile Diabetes 
Foundation International to provide a resource to researchers in their search for the diabetes genes. 
HBDI says it needs families with diabetes who are willing to fill out a family history questionnaire. 
The URL is<br> 
<a href="http://haven.ios.com/~hbdi/homepage.htm">http://haven.ios.com/~hbdi/homepage.htm</a>
<p>
<li> The Federation of European Nurses in Diabetes (FEND) intends to develop and promote the 
professional status of the diabetes nurse throughout Europe. It also aims to influence European health 
care policy relevant to diabetes care and research, and to promote acceptable standards and equity of 
care for people with diabetes throughout Europe. Its URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.fend.org/">http://www.fend.org/</a>
<p>
<li> The International Diabetes Institute, Australia, has its International Diabetes Web Site. The 
URL is<br>
<a href="http://www.idi.org.au/">http://www.idi.org.au/</a>

<p>
</ol>
<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center SIZE=2 NOSHADE>
<p>
<a> <A HREF="univ.htm"><img alt="[Go to Universities 
and Hospitals Web 
Page]" src ="next.gif"></a> Go to 
<A HREF="univ.htm">Universities and Hospitals
Web Resources Page </A>
<p>
<a> <A HREF="genl.htm"><img alt="[Go to General  
Web Page]" src ="previous.gif"></a> Go back 
to <A HREF="genl.htm">General Page </A><p>
<p>
</blockquote></blockquote>
