<HTML><HEAD>
<META http-equiv="PICS-Label" content='(PICS-1.0
"http://www.classify.org/safesurf/" l gen t for "http://www.mdcc.com" r
(SS~~000 1 SS~~100 1))'>
<TITLE>On-line Resources for Diabetics: Universities and Hospitals Web Sites</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#DFFFFF" background="bd2.gif"TEXT="#000000" link="000088" alink="CC6600" vlink="CC6600">
<a name="top"></a><a name="_top"></a>
<table>
<td>
<IMG src="spinstar.gif" height=47 width=47 ALT=" " align=left>
</td><td>
<h2><strong>
<font SIZE="+3"><A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font>
<br>
<FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">
On-line Resources for Diabetics
</FONT>
</td><br>
</table>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" width=100% Height=2 ALT=" ">
</h2></strong>
<center>
<h2>Universities and Hospitals Web Sites</h2>
<h3><b>By Rick Mendosa</b>
<br>(Used with Permission)</h3>
Most Recent Update: January 28, 1997
</center>

<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center SIZE=2 NOSHADE>

<blockquote><blockquote>

<p>

<A HREF ="t.gif"></a><img src="t.gif" align=left alt=T>his Web page brings 

together in one place descriptions of and links to only those Web pages of universities and 

hospitals dealing with diabetes, 

but is linked to the seven other On-line Resources for Diabetes pages dealing with other Web pages,

other parts of the Internet, and other on-line services. Those links that I think are especially valuable are marked 

in <FONT COLOR="Red">red.</FONT>

<p>

<ol>

<li>The Institut for Diabetes Vuk Vhrovac, Zagreb, Croatia, has technical papers of its research staff.

<p>

If you have a SLIP/PPP account or lynx or similiar tools on a dial-up account, the URL is <br>

<a href="gopher://indija.idb.hr/11/eng/lokalni-info">gopher://indija.idb.hr/11/eng/lokalni-info</a>

<p>

Otherwise, gopher indija.idb.hr, choose the English language (unless you prefer Croatian) and select &quot;Information - Institute for diabetes Zagreb/&quot;.

<p>

<li>The Diabetes Research International Network (DRInet) in cooperation with Medical Networking Services at

 the University of Miami School of Medicine has established a gopher file server to provide Internet access to 

diabetes research materials and resources. 

<p>

If you have a SLIP/PPP account or lynx or similiar tools on a dial-up account, the

 URL is<br>

<a href="gopher://drinet.med.miami.edu/1">gopher://drinet.med.miami.edu/1</a>

<p>

Otherwise, gopher drinet.med.miami.edu.

<p>

<li>The Missouri Diabetes Resource Directory is a clearing house for diabetes resources, assistance,

 information and events in Missouri. Its URL is

<br>

<a href="http://www.hsc.missouri.edu/modiabetes/index.html">http://www.hsc.missouri.edu/modiabetes/index.html</a>

<p>

<li>The University of Utah Medical School can show you microscopic views of the pancreas, kidneys, eyes, 

and other tissues of diabetic patients. These images of the "Pathology of Diabetes Mellitus" 

illustrate why good control is important. Its URL is<br>

<a href="http://www-medlib.med.utah.edu/WebPath/DIABETES.html">http://www-medlib.med.utah.edu/WebPath/DIABETES.html</a>

<p>

<li>The pages of the Joslin Diabetes Center DNA Core Facility offer information on

    DNA sequencing, DNA synthesis and DNA Fragment Analysis and how the Core

    provides these services. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://core1.joslab.harvard.edu/core/welcome.html">http://core1.joslab.harvard.edu/core/welcome.html</a>

<p>

<li>The Walter and Eliza Hall Institute of Medical Research in Melbourne, Australia includes a slide show 

explaining in lay terms the development of diabetes research there. The URL is <br>

<a href="http://www.wehi.edu.au/WEHI_Research/burnet/diabetes/">http://www.wehi.edu.au/WEHI_Research/burnet/diabetes/</a>

<p>

<li>John P. Robarts Research Institute Autoimmunity/Diabetes Group introduces some scientists who are 

working to find a cure for diabetes. The URL is <br>

<a href="http://www.rri.uwo.ca/auto/">http://www.rri.uwo.ca/auto/ </a>

<p>

<li>The Diabetes Research and Training Center of the Albert Einstein College of Medicine at Yeshiva 

University in New York serves as a resource for the diabetes research and clinical care communities. Its

home page includes four software programs for diabetics, including &quot;Prescribing the Diabetic Diet,&quot;

&quot;Twenty Questions on the Diabetic Diet&quot; and two series of case studies.The URL is <br>

<a href="http://www.aecom.yu.edu/diabetes/">http://www.aecom.yu.edu/diabetes/</a>

<p>

<li>The Department of Anaesthesia in Basel, Switzerland, includes the &quot;Resident's 

Electronic Handbook for Diabetes mellitus.&quot; Its URL is <br>

<a href="http://www.medana.unibas.ch/eng/amnesix1/diab_1.htm">http://www.medana.unibas.ch/eng/amnesix1/diab_1.htm</a>

<p>

<li>The University of Kansas Medical School Dykes Library's Medical Matrix has a brief list of Internet

 resources for diabetics that was not current when I viewed it. 

Its URL is<br>

<a href="http://kuhttp.cc.ukans.edu/cwis/units/medcntr/Lee/DISEASE/DIABETES.HTML">http://kuhttp.

cc.ukans.edu/cwis/units/medcntr/Lee/DISEASE/DIABETES.HTML</a>

<p>

<li>Ohio State University has hypertext versions of the five Usenet FAQs on diabetes on-line. The URL is

<br>

<a href="http://www.cis.ohio-state.edu/hypertext/faq/usenet/diabetes/faq/top.html">http://www.cis.

ohio-state.edu/hypertext/faq/usenet/diabetes/faq/top.html</a>

<p>

<li>Brian Jackson,  a representative of the University of Texas Student Health Center put together a Diabetes 

Page as a class project. Its URL is

<br>

<a href="http://ccwf.cc.utexas.edu/~bjackson/UTHealth/diabetes.html">http://ccwf.cc.utexas.edu/~bjackson/UTHealth/diabetes.html</a>

<p>

<li>The University of Texas-Houston's Office of Public Affairs  has &quot;UT-Houston News about 

Diabetes&quot; available on-line. Its URL is

<br>

<a href="http://oac3.hsc.uth.tmc.edu/pub_affairs/news/subjects/diabetes.html">http://oac3.hsc.uth.tmc.edu/pub_affairs/

news/subjects/diabetes.html</a>

<p>

<li><FONT COLOR="Red">&quot;Ask NOAH About: Diabetes&quot;</FONT COLOR> is a part of NOAH: New York Online Access of

 CUNY (City University of New York) in both English and Spanish. It has detailed information about 

diabetes at<br>

<a href="http://www.noah.cuny.edu/diabetes/diabetes.html">http://www.noah.cuny.edu/diabetes/diabetes.html</a>

<p>

<li>An article &quot;Mapping Disease Susceptibility Genes - NIDDM&quot; by Stephen S. Rich, Ph.D., is 

on line at <br>

<a href="http://www.nmsr.labmed.umn.edu/nmsr/Diabetes.html">http://www.nmsr.labmed.umn.edu/nmsr/Diabetes.html</a>

<p>

<li>&quot;Screening for Diabetes Mellitus&quot; is an extensive discussion of the need for and efficacy of 

screening for the disease prepared by the Health Sciences Division of Columbia University and the

 Presbyterian Hospital in  New York. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://cpmcnet.columbia.edu/health.sci/.gcps/gcps021.html">http://cpmcnet.columbia.edu/health.sci/.gcps/gcps021.html</a>

<p>

<li>The College of Agricultural and Environmental Sciences of the University of Georgia Cooperative

 Extension Service in Athens, Georgia, publishes &quot;Diabetes Life Lines.&quot; The Summer 1995 issue

 of the  newsletter on &quot;Medication, Exercise, Diet&quot; is available on line at<br>

<a href="gopher://psupena.psu.edu:70/0$d%20121011664">gopher://psupena.psu.edu:70/0$d%20121011664</a>

<p>

<li>Many articles on diabetes are available by gopher from Penn State. The URL is<br>

<a href="gopher://psupena.psu.edu:70/7$k?Diabetes">gopher://psupena.psu.edu:70/7$k?Diabetes</a>

<p>

<li>The mission of the Academy for the Advancement of Diabetes Research and Treatment is to develop the 

Diabetes Research International Network (DRInet) to optimize information transfer in the field of diabetes,

including islet transplantation. Its URL is<br>

<a href="http://drinet.med.miami.edu/">http://drinet.med.miami.edu/</a>

<p>

<li>Kidney Patients' Resources maintains a good directory of resources for diabetics at <br>

<a href="http://www.cc.utah.edu/~cla6202/KPR.htm#3">http://www.cc.utah.edu/~cla6202/KPR.htm#3</a>

<p> 

<li>&quot;Mapping Disease Susceptibility Genes - NIDDM&quot; is a technical paper by  

Stephen S. Rich, Ph.D. The URL is<br>

<a href="gopher://dragon.labmed.umn.edu:70/00/nmsr/highlights/Diabetes">gopher://dragon.labmed.umn.edu:70/00/nmsr/highlights/Diabetes</a>

<p>

<li>The Diabetes Research & Treatment Centre is an interdisciplinary center whose function is to promote 

research, education and treatment of diabetes in Manitoba. It has some good information at<br>

<a href="http://www.umanitoba.ca/faculties/medicine/DRTC/">http://www.umanitoba.ca/faculties/medicine/DRTC/</a>

<p>

<li>Projekt-D is a model project funded by the Bundesgesundheitsministerium, Bonn, Germany, focusing on

 young Type I patients. The work is done at the university's hospital for children and adolescents, 

Erlangen, Germany.  Dr. Christian Renner (who also runs the diabetes-max mailing list) maintains the 

URL at<br>

<a href="http://www.well.com/user/cjrenner/index.html">http://www.well.com/user/cjrenner/index.html</a>

<p>

<li><i>The Family Practice Handbook</i> by Mark A. Graber, M.D., Rhea J. Allen, M.D., Co-Chief Resident, 

and Barcey T. Levy, M.D., Co-Chief Resident, all of the Department of Family Practice, University of Iowa College of 

Medicine, Iowa City, Iowa, has valuable sections in chapter 5 on hypoglycemia, diabetes mellitus,  diabetic 

ketoacidosis, and hyperglycemic-nyperosmolar nonketotic syndrome. Start at<br>

<a href="http://indy.radiology.uiowa.edu/Providers/ClinRef/FPHandbook/05.html">http://indy.radiology.uiowa.edu/Providers/ClinRef/FPHandbook/05.html</a>

<p>

<li>Diabetes Research and Education Centre Trust (DIRECT) is a registered charity founded in 1990 to promote 

Exeter-based research into the cause and prevention of the complications of diabetes, and to provide teaching and 

support to enable patients to best manage their own condition. DIRECT supports local research initiatives and helps 

foster the development of a leading world center for diabetes research and education in Devon.

In the last seven years educational programs for diabetic patients and health care workers have been established; a team 

of 20 researchers with unique equipment has been built up working from the Diabetes Research Centre, funded by 

the charity in the grounds of the Postgraduate Medical School, Royal Devon and Exeter Hospital, Wonford. The 

URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.ex.ac.uk/~tjbacon/dm/direct.html">http://www.ex.ac.uk/~tjbacon/dm/direct.html</a>

<p>

<LI>The Diabetes Center of  the University of Leipzig, Germany (Universit&auml;t Leipzig), headed 

by <A HREF="mailto:shew@server3.medizin.uni-leipzig.de">Professor Werner Scherbaum</A>,

M.D., director of the Department of Internal Medicine, University Hospital of Leipzig, 

has a diabetes Web site in both German and English. Click on the British flag to go to the English-language site.

The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://http://www.uni-leipzig.de/~diabetes/">http://www.uni-leipzig.de/~diabetes/</A>

<p>

<li> The University of California, Davis, has lots of on-line information about diabetes, including particularly 

an article by Arthur C. Huntley, M.D., in <i>Dermatology Online Journal, </i> December 1995, reviewing 

skin manifestations of diabetes. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://matrix.ucdavis.edu/DOJvol1num2/diabetes/dmreview.html">http://matrix.ucdavis.edu/DOJvol1num2/diabetes/dmreview.html</a>

<p>

Other articles from <i>Dermatology Online Journal</i> dealing with dermatology and diabetes can be found at<br>

<a href="http://matrix.ucdavis.edu/DOJ.html">http://matrix.ucdavis.edu/DOJ.html</a>

<p>

<li> The Joslin Diabetes Center is an international leader in diabetes research, treatment,and patient and professional 

education established in 1898 in Boston, Massachusetts. Joslin is affiliated with Harvard Medical School. Many 

important innovations in diabetes research, including laser treatment for diabetic eye disease, strategies for 

identifying and perhaps preventing Type I diabetes, and strategies to enable women with diabetes to give birth to 

healthy babies were developed with the help of clinical staff and researchers at Joslin. The site include an

extensive Online Diabetes Library of several documents (but no search engine). The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.joslin.harvard.edu/">http://www.joslin.harvard.edu/</a>

<p>

<li> It's not too clear, but apparently this is individual course material for Biology 101 -- Introduction to Biotechnology, on 

&quot;Diabetes and Insulin, 1996&quot; at Case Western Reserve University. The URL is<br> 

<a href="http://litwww.cwru.edu/CWRU/Dept/Artsci/biol/courses/101/diabet96.htm">http://litwww.cwru.edu/CWRU/Dept/Artsci/biol/courses/101/diabet96.htm</a>

<p>

<li >The May/June 1995 issue of the Newsletter of the Alberta Heritage Foundation for Medical Research in Edmonton, 

Alberta, Canada, includes an article, &quot;Gene Therapy for Diabetes?&quot; by University of Calgary researcher 

Dr. Irene Wanke, who is genetically engineering the liver to serve as a pancreas, so that insulin can be produced in 

response to glucose levels. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.worldweb.com/ahfmr/may/diabetes.html">http://www.worldweb.com/ahfmr/may/diabetes.html</a>

<p>

<li> The Jack and Lucy Clark Department of Pediatrics of New York's Mount Sinai Hospital has a 

Web page on Pediatric Endocrinology and Metabolism at <br>

<a href="http://www.mssm.edu/peds/iddm-inf.html">http://www.mssm.edu/peds/iddm-inf.html</a>

<p>

<li> The Diabetes Prevention Trial is a national study running from 1994 to the year 2000 to test if it's 

possible to prevent or delay the onset of Type 1.  Information on the trial 

can be found at Stanford University's School of Medicine site. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www-med.stanford.edu/school/DPT1.html">http://www-med.stanford.edu/school/DPT1.html</a>

<p>

<li> &quot;Stressors and their Moderators as Related to Behavior Problems in Children with 

Diabetes&quot; is Zhinuan Hu's thesis. The URL is<br>

http://studentweb.tulane.edu/~zhinuan/thesis1.html

</ol>
<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center SIZE=2 NOSHADE>
<p>
