<h2><strong>
<font SIZE="+3"><A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font>
<br>
<FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">
On-line Resources for Diabetics
</FONT>
</td><br>
</table>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" width=100% Height=2 ALT=" ">
</h2></strong>
<center>
<h2>Company Web Sites</h2><br>
<h3><b>By Rick Mendosa</b>
<br>(Used with Permission)</h3>

Most Recent Update: January 28, 1997

<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center SIZE=2 NOSHADE></P></CENTER>



<BLOCKQUOTE>

<BLOCKQUOTE>

<P><IMG SRC="t.gif" ALT="T" HEIGHT=34 WIDTH=31 ALIGN=LEFT>his Web page

brings together in one place descriptions of and links to only those company

Web pages dealing with diabetes, but is linked to the seven other On-line

Resources for Diabetes pages dealing with other Web pages, other parts

of the Internet, and other on-line services. Those links that I think are

especially valuable are marked in <FONT COLOR="#FF0000">red.</FONT> </P>



<P>Many companies now use the World Wide Web to advertise their products

and services. Businesses catering to diabetics include: </P>



<OL>

<LI>The Wright Prefilled Syringe Case is for people on the go. Its URL

is<BR>

<A HREF="http://maingate.net/mall/hpncos/wright.html">http://maingate.net/mall/hpncos/wright.html</A>

<p>



<LI>The Foot &amp; Ankle Institute of St. George (Utah) focuses on &quot;The

Diabetic Foot&quot; with considerable information about diabetic ulcers

and neuropathy. Run by Dr. Keith Reber, this site can be found at<BR>

<A HREF="http://infowest.com/doctor/">http://infowest.com/doctor/ </A>

<p>

<LI>Columbia/HCA Healthcare Corporation as the nation's largest healthcare

services provider also has a Web page with lots of consumer health information.

For example, it links a page from The West Georgia Center for Metabolic

Disorders at Columbia Doctors Hospital in Columbus, Georgia, that offers

a synopsis of recent information on metabolic disorders including news

of recent advances in treating diabetes. That link is <BR>

<A HREF="http://www.columbia-hca.com/phys/met.html#diabetes">http://www.columbia-hca.com/phys/met.html#

diabetes.</A> Also available is an AOL chat transcript about diabetes with

Dr. Rick Abrams. The URL for Columbia/HCA Healthcare Corporation itself

is <BR>

<A HREF="http://www.columbia-hca.com/">http://www.columbia-hca.com/</A>

<p>



<LI>MiniMed Technologies in Sylmar, California, one of the major manufacturers

of insulin pumps has a lot of information about them on line. You can find

it at<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.minimed.com/">http://www.minimed.com/ </A>

<p>

<LI>Oxystat Home Health Care Systems is a physician managed health care

company with supplies and accessories for the patient with diabetes. Its

site is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.oxystat.com/diabetes/">http://www.oxystat.com/diabetes/</A>

<p>



<LI>The Diabetes Mall contains information on subjects such as flexible

insulin therapy, secrets of diabetes math and carb counting, mechanisms

to prevent complications, and a reference book, cookbook, and software

section. It's located at<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.diabetesnet.com/index.html">http://www.diabetesnet.com/index.html</A>

<p>



<LI>National Applied Science is a company specializing in implantable biosensor

devices. Its home page includes two articles about diabetes, &quot;A Brief

History of Diabetes&quot; and &quot;Information on Diabetes.&quot; The

URL is <BR>

<A HREF="http://www.napplisci.com/welcome.html">http://www.napplisci.com/welcome.html</A>

<p>



<LI>NutraSweet's FAQ includes some information directed to diabetics. Its

URL is <BR>

<A HREF="http://www.nutrasweet.com/library.html">http://www.nutrasweet.com/library.html</A>

<p>



<LI>Electronic Waveform Lab Inc. in Huntington Beach, California describes

its H-Wave machine, which is a device that uses electro-therapy to treat

pain caused by diabetic neuropathy. Its URL is <BR>

<A HREF="http://www.inetbiz.com/h-wave/">http://www.inetbiz.com/h-wave/</A>

<p>



<LI>NutriGenie, a nutrition software publisher has two Windows programs

for diabetics, &quot;Managing Diabetes,&quot; a comprehensive diabetes

management system, and &quot;Diabetes Nutrition,&quot; a less complete

and less expensive version. Its URL is <BR>

<A HREF="http://pages.prodigy.com/CA/nutrigenie/">http://pages.prodigy.com/CA/nutrigenie/</A>

<p>



<LI>Diabetic Assistance Program of NY was formed to make it easy for diabetic

patients to get their monthly diabetic supplies without paperwork. It also

provides educational material showing average responses to different insulins.

Its URL includes a table &quot;Insulin Responses&quot; and &quot;Basic

Facts About Diabetes.&quot; Its URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://world-wide.com/DAPNY/">http://world-wide.com/DAPNY/</A>

<p>



<LI>BioStore International has a Windows data management tool for diabetics

called &quot;BioStore&reg; Pro.&quot; Its URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www/bizscape.com/biostore">http://www/bizscape.com/biostore</A>

<p>



<LI>Chronimed Inc. in Minnetonka, Minnesota, is a health care company focusing

on the needs of people with chronic conditions. Its Internet site focuses

on the needs of diabetics, including some information and an on-line pharmacy.

Its URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.chronimed.com/">http://www.chronimed.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>Preferred Rx of Solon, Ohio, specializes in assisting diabetics received

their medications and supplies. Its URL is <BR>

<A HREF="http://www.cybergate.net/~cjmele/">http://www.cybergate.net/~cjmele/</A>

<p>



<LI>ITA Software Inc.'s Diabetes Online Software Services homepage allows

users to view its diabetes software. Its URL is <BR>

<A HREF="http://www.syix.com/doss/index.html">http://www.syix.com/doss/index.html</A>

<p>



<LI>Med-Safe Systems Inc. in Oceanside, California, specializes in the

safe disposal of used syringes. Its URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.electriciti.com/~markt/indx.html">http://www.electriciti.com/~markt/indx.html</A>

<p>



<LI>Medicool Inc. in Torrance, California, provides a wide range of products

related to diabetes care. The company manufactures two traveling cases

that insure proper insulin temperature. It also distributes items not easily

found in pharmacies and home health care stores, including books and videos

as well as a multi-vitamin formulated specifically for persons with diabetes.

The site also has an info page with late-breaking diabetes news. Its URL

is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.medicool.com/">http://www.medicool.com/</A> 

<p>

<li> Medicool's Diabetes News Archives is an important page at Medicool's site that is not 

readily accessible from its home page. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.medicool.com/archive.html">http://www.medicool.com/archive.html</a>



<p>

<LI>&quot;Managing Your Child's Diabetes&quot; is information about a book

of that name that you can buy. Its URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.sapphire.com/UNCAT/uncat67.html">http://www.sapphire.com/UNCAT/uncat67.html</A>

<p>



<LI>The Gerson Therapy Home Page includes an article &quot;The Cure and

Prevention of Diabetes&quot; by Charlotte Gerson, president of The Gerson

Institute in Bonita, California. Its URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.gerson.org">http://www.gerson.org</A> 

<p>



<LI>National Health Video Inc. has a Diabetes Page where each week it posts

three tips on diabetes management. Its URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.nhv.com/nhv/diabetes.htm">http://www.nhv.com/nhv/diabetes.htm</A>

<p>



<LI>Universal Self Care Inc. of Livonia, Michigan, through its subsidiary

Diabetes Self Care (formerly known as Patient Care Services, Sugar Free

Centers and The Thriftee Group), is a specialty provider of supplies and

support services for individuals with diabetes. Its URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.mvisibility.com/usci/">http://www.mvisibility.com/usci/</A>

<p>



<LI>Adobe Springs water provides some articles about the effects of most

bottled waters of magnesium deficiency on diseases including diabetes.

The URL is <BR>

<A HREF="http://www.execpc.com/~magnesum/articles.html">http://www.execpc.com/~magnesum/articles.html</A>

<p>



<LI>Ruth E. Lundstrom and others at the University of Massachusetts Medical

Center prepared the <I>Healing Hands Handbook for Persons with Diabetes.</I>

Spiral bound copies are $14.95 plus $5 for shipping. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.stonehand.com/hh/title_pg.htm">http://www.stonehand.com/hh/title_pg.htm</A>

<p>



<LI>Podiatrist Todd Horton says he has developed a product that can relieve

vascular and diabetic neuropathy of the foot and leg. It helps burning

feet and cold feet, gravel and prickly sensations, and numbness. The URL

is<BR>

<A HREF="http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/todd_horton/">http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/todd_horton/</A>

<p>



<LI>Eli Lilly and Company has a pilot Web site &quot;Managing Your Diabetes,&quot;

which provides diabetes information and services for individuals in the

U.S. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.lilly.com/diabetes/">http://www.lilly.com/diabetes/</A>

<p>



<LI>Rainbow Valley Communication Inc. produces videos and companion products

to help patients interact with medical professionals and be more effective

in daily lifestyle changes. They sell a video and workbook called &quot;Day

to Day Living with Diabetes Type II&quot; and a refrigerator magnet to

help you chart your blood sugar levels. They also provide information on

diabetes complications. Their URL is <BR>

<A HREF="http://www.rvci.com/">http://www.rvci.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>Biobr&aacute;s is the Web site of a publicly-traded company headquartered

in Belo Horizonte, Brazil, that manufactures insulin, Metformin, and other

products for diabetes. The site has information about the company and about

diabetes generally in English, Spanish and Portuguese. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.biobras.com/">http://www.biobras.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>Liberty Medical Supply provides sales, service and supply of diabetic

supplies at little to no cost to its customers. Its URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.libmed.com/">http://www.libmed.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>Jeffrey Stone works with people who have chronic foot wounds, that

is, wounds that have gone unhealed for more than two months. Many of the

people Stone sees have diabetes. On average, the wounds of his patients

with diabetes have been present for 11.8 months, and some have been there

for years. Stone thinks that hyperbaric oxygen (HBO) therapy can help these

wounds heal. During HBO therapy, a patient breathes oxygen at increased

atmospheric pressure. The URL for his page is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.wound.com/">http://www.wound.com/</A> 



<P>The site also includes a paper, &quot;The Role of Hyperbaric Oxygen

in the Treatment of Diabetic Foot Wounds,&quot; by Jeff A. Stone, et al,

reprinted from the May 1995 issue of <I>Diabetes.</I> That URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.wound.com/research.html#foot">http://www.wound.com/research.html#foot</A>

</P>

<p>



<LI>The Electric Library has millions of articles and other documents on-line

available for downloading. While this is a fee service, a two-week trial

membership good for 100 searches is free. In one search I found more than

150 articles on diabetes dating from recent months back to 1991. Most were

from <I>Diabetes Forecast, Diabetes in the News</I>, and the <I>Los Angeles

Times</I>. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.elibrary.com/">http://www.elibrary.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>The Vigora Diabetes Health Home Page features &quot;Software That Makes

The Control of Diabetes Easier.&quot; Here are three programs: The Diabetes

Mentor computerizes and graphs your diabetes-related measurements, helping

you adjust your regime to achieve targeted BGs; The Diabetes COP helps

you maintain control of your blood sugars, keeps you organized and may

thereby help prevent early onset of BGM; BGM v1.2TM interfaces with your

Lifescan Profile and One-Touch II meter to graph BGs on your PC. The URL

is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.halcyon.com/vigora">http://www.halcyon.com/vigora</A>

<p>



<LI>The Medi-Ject Corporation's site is designed for persons with diabetes

who inject insulin. The site also has information on needle-free drug delivery

technology plus a diabetes university section with links to other sites.

Its URL is <BR>

<A HREF="http://www.mediject.com">http://www.mediject.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>Disetronic Holding AG is a manufacturer of medical devices headquartered

in Burgdorf, Switzerland. Disetronic Medical Systems Inc., is the wholly-owned

subsidiary &quot;housing the heart of the business,&quot; including including

insulin pumps. The business area &quot;Infusion Systems&quot; develops,

manufactures and markets microdosage and peristaltic pumps together with

their related consumables. The pumps are usually sold under the Disetronic

label directly to patients and health organizations. Disetronic says it

currently has the largest market share worldwide for insulin pump therapy

for the treatment of diabetes. The business area &quot;Injection Systems&quot;

develops and manufactures injection pens and sterile needles. The pens

are usually supplied directly to pharmaceutical companies. In the new business

area of &quot;Sensors&quot; Disetronic is working on long-term blood pressure

and blood glucose measurement. The company's URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.hb9eh.ch/disetron/">http://www.hb9eh.ch/disetron/</A>

<p>



<LI>If you believe that diabetics should stay away from sugar, you might

like the Diabetic Emporium &amp; Confectionery Shoppe Ltd., of Johnson

City, New York. They say that everything this on-line store sells is &quot;safe

for a diabetic to eat&quot; apparently because it is sugar-free or has

no added sugar. The site also has nutritional facts documents which may

be downloaded. These documents include fat content, calories, sweetner

used, serving size, and whether kosher or not. The URL for this company

is<BR>

<A HREF="http://204.249.117.52:80/deacs/">http://204.249.117.52:80/deacs/</A>

<p>



It is also reachable with <BR>

<A HREF="http://www.tier.net/deacs">http://www.tier.net/deacs</A>

<p>



<LI>Diabetes Online Software Services describes all five computer programs

included with ITA Software Inc.'s software bundle called Diabetes Works.

You can also take an educational tour to learn about insulin coverages,

read updates about the remarkable Jack McCarthy, 60 years insulin dependent,

who is <I>right now</I> walking 1,431 miles from Kansas to the Olympic

Games in Atlanta, and see pictures of him. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.diabetesonline.com/">http://www.diabetesonline.com/</A>

<p>



<LI>MediLife's Personal Diabetes Center has a free demo of <I>Balance PC,</I>

a Windows<SUP>TM</SUP>-based product that offers total disease management

for individuals with diabetes. Here too you will find risk tests, more

than 250 articles on diabetes, and diabetes trivia. Or you can pose any

questions you have about diabetes to a diabetes nurse educator. The URL

is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.medilife.com/medilife/diabetes/index.htm">http://www.medilife.com/medilife/diabetes/index.htm</A>

<p>



<LI>Diabetes Network in Japan, sponsored by the Soshinsha company and supported

by a commitee of the Japan Association for Diabetes, is the first diabetes

Web site in Japanese. To view this site Soshinsha suggests that you use

the font &quot;Osaka.&quot; The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.so-net.or.jp/vivre/soshin/dm-net.htm">http://www.so-net.or.jp/vivre/soshin/dm-net.htm</A>

<p>



<LI>Another new site that specializes in sugar-free foods is Sweet Health.

Their site says that it &quot;provides at your doorstep the highest quality

sugar-free treats from around the world. Whether you're a diabetic or just

on a sugar-free diet, Sweet Health is the source for these hard-to-get

products.&quot; The URL is <BR>

<A HREF="http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/Sweet_Health/">http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/Sweet_Health/</A>

<p>



<LI>Diabtrends is the product of a small Swiss software company. The Web

site says that &quot;FIT [Flexible Insulin Therapy] is a new way to understand

and manage the disease....The software is composed of two elements: The

Windows shareware Diabass monitoring and management system...[and] the

plug-in Diabtrends mobile device for the on-line data recall and control

of the FIT therapy parameters, our product...FIT is selfcare in collaboration

with medical and therapeutic staffs.&quot; Currently, information is available

on the personal home page of <A HREF="mailto:spectrum@mail.spiderweb.ch">Patrick

Auderset, also known as Dito,</A> who says that an official site, <A HREF="www.diabtrends.com">www.diabtrends.com</A>

will be available soon. The current URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/ditos/">http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/ditos/</A>

<p>



<LI>The leading maker of blood glucose monitoring systems, LifeScan, now

has a Web page. Its URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.lifescan.com/">http://www.lifescan.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI><I>Diabetic Meal Planning Made Easy!</I> was written by Marilyn White,

an insulin-using diabetic, who was trained in meal planning by a registered

dietitian. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.softdisk.com/customer/moffat9/">http://www.softdisk.com/customer/moffat9/</A>

<p>



<LI>Medical Foods Inc. in Cambridge, Massachusetts, has introduced <I>The

NiteBite</I> snack bar. It is, they say, &quot; an innovative, scientifically-designed

food for the nutritional management of hypoglycemia (low blood sugar, or

glucose). Unlike conventional snacks and other products marketed to people

with diabetes for the control of blood glucose, NiteBite is designed to

significantly reduce the risk of developing hypoglycemia without causing

hyperglycemia (high blood sugar, or glucose). Formulated with a tasty,

chocolate fudge-flavor, the NiteBite snack bar supplies timed-release glucose

where it lasts 6 hours or more...&quot; They also say that you can order

a free sampler by calling toll-free 1-888-342-5634. Their URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.pslgroup.com/dg/9f4e.htm">http://www.pslgroup.com/dg/9f4e.htm</A>

<p>



<LI>Wes-Bar Press specializes in books to help diabetics lead a healthy

lifestyle through good nutrition. Its Web site is at<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.smartnet.net/~wes-bar/">http://www.smartnet.net/~wes-bar/</A>

<p>



<LI>The sugarfree-dot-com health center is the site under construction

for a company called Smile, which says that it makes the best naturally

sweetened candies you'll ever taste. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.sugarfree.com/">http://www.sugarfree.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>Understanding Diabetes is a Web page of HealthWorks, a new addition

to the Web site of Health Communication Network Ltd, in St Leonards, New

South Wales, Australia. HealthWorks is a collection of electronic books

about common health problems. Each one has been written by an Australian

author in an easy-to-read style. A subscription to any of these books gives

access to the whole book for browsing, downloading or printing. You can

browse the tables of contents and information about the author before purchase.

The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.hcn.net.au/healthworks/contentsd.html">http://www.hcn.net.au/healthworks/contentsd.html</A>

<p>



<LI>RxHealth.com Canada, a new drug and disease information service, contains

diabetes information and links. It contains information on several diseases,

including diabetes, and on the treatment of them. In addition, the service

offers its clients consultation with licensed Canadian pharmacists. Its

intention is to expand its focus in the future to provide this information

worldwide, but at the moment, it is on helping Canadians. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.RxHealth.com/">http://www.RxHealth.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>This is the September 1978 press release from Genentech Inc., &quot;First

Successful Laboratory Production of Human Insulin Announced.&quot; The

URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.gene.com/pressrelease/1981/9_6_78.html">http://www.gene.com/pressrelease/1981/9_6_78.html</A>

<p>



<LI><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Diabetes.com</FONT> is a comprehensive Web resource

published by Matthew Naythons, M.D., and the staff of NetHealth, publisher

of the Internet Health, Fitness, and Medicine Yellow Pages (Osborne McGraw

Hill). NetHealth is a division of Epicenter Communications Inc. The URL

is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.diabetes.com/">http://www.diabetes.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>InfoDek Inc. in Atlanta, Georgia, produces information &quot;Deks&quot;

which, they say, contain reliable and up-to-date information about a particular

topic and are written in a brief and simple outline form. The DiabetesDek

is a pocket-sized reference tool that serves as a day-to-day guide for

diabetes management. Topics include what diabetes is, the basic types of

diabetes, checking your blood glucose, diabetes management, insulin, oral

diabetes medicines, meal planning, exercise, sick day guidelines, hypoglycemia,

hyperglycemia, tips for traveling, long-term concerns and how to get the

care you need. They have some sort of tie-in to Lifescan, since that company

name appears on the site. InfoDek has two diabetes publications, DiabetesDek

Consumer and DiabetesDek Professional. Each are $11.95. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.infodek.com/diabetesindex.html">http://www.infodek.com/diabetesindex.html</A>

<p>



<LI>Diabetes Care is the Web site of Boehringer Mannheim Corp., the world's

largest manufacturer of home blood glucose monitors for patients with diabetes.

The site provides information about the company's products at<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.boehringer-mannheim.com/diabetes/diabetes.htm">http://www.boehringer-mannheim.com/diabetes/diabetes.htm

</A>

<p>



<LI>SpectRx Inc. in Norcross, Georgia, is a medical technology development

company that specializes in minimally and non-invasive diagnostic and monitoring

systems. Programs currently under development by SpectRx are a painless,

bloodless personal glucose monitor, a non-invasive bilirubin testing device

and a non-invasive diabetes screening device. SpectRx controls 30 granted

or pending patents related to minimally and non-invasive medical technology

and more sensitive, point-of-care invasive diagnostic tests using fluorescence

lifetime spectroscopy. The company has research and development arrangements

with 15 universities, research institutions and hospitals worldwide. The

site has considerable information about the company, its programs, and

links to other sites of interest to diabetics. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.spectrx.com/">http://www.spectrx.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>Metertech Inc. designs and manufactures medical and analytical instruments

in Taiwan. One of its products is the Sensorex blood glucose monitoring

system, which is described on the company's Web page at <BR>

<A HREF="http://www.asiannet.com/taiwan/metertech">http://www.asiannet.com/taiwan/metertech

</A>

<p>



<LI>The Diabetic Supply Catalog of Edgepark Surgical Inc. is another place

to order diabetic supplies on-line. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.edgepark.com/catalog.html">http://www.edgepark.com/catalog.html</A>

<p>



<LI>Amylin Pharmaceuticals Inc. is a biopharmaceutical company in San Diego,

California, that is developing new medicines to better manage diabetes.

The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.amylin.com/">http://www.amylin.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>Teresa Snow, a parent of a diabetic child, founded Sugarfree Candy

Express in Salt Lake City to find the best sugarfree candy. Some of the

candies she sells are also fat-free. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.sugarfreecandy.com/">http://www.sugarfreecandy.com/</A>

<p>



<LI>Baker Norton Pharmaceuticals Inc. in Miami, Florida, sells Zbar, the

&quot;Long Acting Carbohydrate Snack&quot; to reduce episodes of low blood

sugar. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.zbar.com/">http://www.zbar.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>Terron Inc. of Sanger, Texas, sells the &quot;Ident-A-Cap&quot; to

make vial identification a snap for IDD patients, including those who are

visually impaired. <A HREF="mailto:identcap@iglobal.net">Terry Jones,</A>

a pharmacist and Terron's president, created the Ident-A-Caps to prevent

accidental and sometimes fatal dosing from the wrong insulin vial due to

similar labeling. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.ident-a-cap.com/">http://www.ident-a-cap.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>Diabetic Insulcap Inc. in Roseville, California, developed and manufactures

the &quot;Insulcap&quot; which is used by adults and juveniles as an aid

in withdrawing insulin. It also benefits those with visual and physical

limitations. The Web site shows the use of the product. <A HREF="mailto:Insulcap@ix.Netcom.Com">Karen

Holtz</A> heads sales and marketing. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.Insulcap.com/">http://www.Insulcap.com/</A> 

<p>



<LI>U.S. Healthcare&reg; and Aetna Plans &reg; provide a library of information

on a wide variety of health topics, including diabetes. General, perhaps

useful, the information is not up-to-date. The diabetes page notes that

&quot;The above information was compiled in February 1994&quot;. The URL

is <A HREF="http://www.ushc.com/health/5610.html">http://www.ushc.com/health/5610.html

</A>

<p>



<LI>Unlike a lot of companies on the Web, Universal Self Care Inc. in Roanoke,

Virigina, offers lots of information about diabetes, including a comprehensive

overview of the DCCT, while trying to get you to buy its services. Universal

Self Care is national pharmacy provider, pharmacy benefit manager and specialty

supplier of diabetes products and self-management services. The URL is<BR>

<A HREF="http://www.theroanoketimes.com/universal/index.html">http://www.theroanoketimes.com/universal/index.html</A>

<p>



<LI>Drug ID International Inc. in San Diego sells &quot;The Quantitator<sup>TM</sup>,&quot;

a PC compatible software computer program for Type I diabetics. It

converts the daily insulin regimen into hourly amounts of insulin released

to the body and tracks the rise and fall of the numerical amounts on a

hard copy printout to anticipate the time when low or high blood sugars

can occur. The URL is<BR>

</A> <A HREF="http://www.electronic-office.com/quantitator/">http://www.electronic-office.com/quantitator/</A>

<p>

<li> Hoechst Marion Roussel, the pharmaceutical division of Germany's Hoechst A.G., developed an oral 

antidiabetic agent called 

glimepiride that the Food and Drug Administration recently approved for use in the United States. It 

was earlier approved in Switzerland, Sweden, the Netherlands, and Denmark. HMR plans to launch 

the product in the U.S. under the brand name Amaryl&reg;. The URL for the company's press 

release is<br>

<a href="http://www.hoechst.com/press_e/glime-e.htm">http://www.hoechst.com/press_e/glime-e.htm</a>

</ol>
<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center SIZE=2 NOSHADE>
<p>
