</td><td>
<h2><strong>
<font SIZE="+3"><A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font>
<br>
<FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">
On-line Resources for Diabetics
</FONT>
</td><br>
</table>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" width=100% Height=2 ALT=" ">
</h2></strong>
<center>
<h2>Publications Web Sites</h2>
<h3><b>By Rick Mendosa</b>
<br>(Used with Permission)</h3>

Most Recent Update: January 28, 1997

</center>

<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center SIZE=2 NOSHADE>

<blockquote><blockquote>

<p>

<A HREF ="t.gif"></a><img src="t.gif" align=left alt=T>his Web page brings 

together in one place descriptions of and links to only those magazine and other publications 

Web pages dealing with diabetes, 

but is linked to the seven other On-line Resources for Diabetes pages dealing with other Web pages,

other parts of the Internet, and other on-line services. Those links that I think are especially valuable are marked 

in <FONT COLOR="Red">red.</FONT>

<p>

<ol>

<li> Here are links to the publications of the American Diabetes Association: <i>Diabetes 

Forecast, Diabetes, Diabetes Care, Diabetes Spectrum, Diabetes Insider, Diabetes Review, Clinical 

Diabetes</i>. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.diabetes.org/Publications/">http://www.diabetes.org/Publications/</a>

<p>

<li> The online bookstore of the American Diabetes Association is now a full-featured online 

ordering site. Two direct links work<br>

<a href="http://www.ada.judds.com/adabooks">http://www.ada.judds.com/adabooks</a>

or

<a href="http://www.judds.com:80/prd.i/pgen/adabooks/UK2N46HSE3SH2JPX00G7BSNC7WXN069R/main.html">http://www.judds.com:80/prd.i/pgen/adabooks/UK2N46HSE3SH2JPX00G7BSNC7WXN069R/main.html</a>

<p>

<li> <i>Diabetes Interview</i> is a meaty

magazine to keep you current on developments in the field. An annual subscription for 12 

months issues mailed every two months is $14. The magazine's URL is

<a href="http://www.diabetesnet.com/diabintv.html">http://www.diabetesnet.com/diabintv.html</a>

<p>

<li> <i>Voice of the Diabetic</i> is a freee quarterly magazine published by The Diabetics Division of the 

National Federation of the Blind. 

 Each issue contains personal, candid stories written by diabetics, friends, health care 

professionals and others who share experiences and expertise on diabetes and its 

complications. Emphasizing the importance of good diabetes control, proper diet, and 

independence, this upbeat outreach publication shows diabetics that they have options 

regardless of the side effects of diabetes. Regular features include a medical Q and A 

column, a &quot;Recipe Corner,&quot; and a resource column of aids and appliances. Its URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.nfb.org/voice.htm">http://www.nfb.org/voice.htm</a>

<p>

<li> A new magazine called <i>Two Types -- The Official Diabetes Lifestyle 

Magazine</i> is about to appear. The premiere issue is scheduled  

for mid-January mailing. Then regularly monthly issues will begin in March. The magazine's 

mission is to present the best looking, most complete, and 

eclectic monthly sources of information to better the lives of those who have diabetes. It 

will be covering pharmaceuticals, new treatments, diabetes education, exercise and recipes

as well as reviewing health spas, restaurants and all forms of exercise- and diabetes-related 

equipment. Annual subscriptions are $34.95. The magazine's URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.twotypes.com/">http://www.twotypes.com/</a>

<p>

<li> <i>Diabetes Self-Management</i>  exists to provide you with a strategy for 

self-management of your diabetes. It also has some articles available on-line. Its URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.enews.com/magazines/diabetes/">http://www.enews.com/magazines/diabetes/</a>

<p>

<li> WebMedLit scans the Web each night for updates to 16 medical journals currently. Some, but not all, 

require that you register first with that journal.  Diabetes/Endocrinology is one of nine areas covered. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.webmedlit.com/">http://www.webmedlit.com/</a>

<p>

<li> The new Web site for <i>Diabetes Interview</i> is at<br>

<a href="http://www.best.com/~diabetes/">http://www.best.com/~diabetes/</a>

<p>

<li>Individual Inc.'s NewsPage contains a section on recent news articles dealing with diabetes. Only the 

first paragraph of each article is available free without a subscription. Its URL is <br>

<a href="http://www.newspage.com/NEWSPAGE/cgi-bin/walk.cgi/NEWSPAGE/info/d15/d8/d18/">

http://www.newspage.com/NEWSPAGE/cgi-bin/walk.cgi/NEWSPAGE/info/d15/d8/d18/</a>

<p>

<li>The article &quot;Metformin Approved for

Non-insulin-dependent Diabetes&quot; is reprinted from the February 1995 issue of <i>Medical Sciences 

Bulletin</i>, published by Pharmaceutical Information Associates, Ltd. The URL is <br>

<a href="http://pharminfo.com/pubs/msb/metform.html">http://pharminfo.com/pubs/msb/metform.html</a>

<p>

<li><i>Philadelphia Magazine</i> has an annual guide of the best specialized medical centers in the 

Philadelphia area. Two &quot;Medical Centers of Excellence&quot for diabetes are profiled at<br>

<a href="http://www.libertynet.org:80/cgi-bin/htgrep-usr/file=philamag/public_html/centers/centers-list.html?toc-Diabetes">http://www.libertynet.org:80/cgi-bin/htgrep-usr/file=philamag/public_html/centers/centers-list.html?toc-Diabetes</a>

<p>

<li>The Pharmaceutical Information Network lets you search for terms like diabetes or 

metformin and will take you to dozens of articles. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://pharminfo.com/">http://pharminfo.com/</a>

<p>

<li>The Diabetic Gourmet is an e-zine designed to provide information and resources for diabetic 

living, with exciting recipes, feature articles, and useful resources. Its motto is &quot;Diabetic Dining 

for the Global Gormet.&quot; The URL is <br>

<a href="http://gourmetconnection.com/ezine/diabetic/">http://gourmetconnection.com/ezine/diabetic/</a>

<p>

<li> James Deighan of the International Clipping Service in Charlottetown, Prince Edward Island, 

Canada, maintains an extensive list of books on diabetes at<br>

<a href="http://www.isn.net/~deighanj/diabets0.html">http://www.isn.net/~deighanj/diabets0.html</a>

<p>

<li> &quot;Intensive Treatment Of Diabetes Pays Off&quot; is an article by Richard A. Know in 

<i>The Boston Globe</i> that is well worth reading. It's at<br>

<a href="http://yourhealthdaily.com/313_110896_114227_4765.html">http://yourhealthdaily.com/313_110896_114227_4765.html</a>

<p>

<li>The EnviroLink Network, an environmental information clearinghouse, has at least two substantial articles

 about diabetes online:

<p>

<ul>



<li>&quot;Diabetes and a Vegetarian Diet&quot; by Virginia Messina, M.P.H., R.D., is a persuasive discussion of the

 advantages of a vegetarian diet for diabetes. The article was originally published in 

<i>Vegetarian Journal Reports</i>. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.envirolink.org/arrs/VRG/diabetes.html">http://www.envirolink.org/arrs/VRG/diabetes.html</a>

<p>

<li>&quot;Diet And Diabetes&quot; is a Physicians Committee for Responsible Medicine fact sheet by Jonathan 

Esterhazy of the Manitoba Animal Rights Coalition. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://envirolink.org/arrs/essays/diabetes.html">http://envirolink.org/arrs/essays/diabetes.html</a>

</a>

</ul>

<p>

<li><i>The Philadelphia Inquirer</i> has an extensive and well-linked article about diabetes on line 

&quot;Tracking the genes to conquer diabetes&quot; at <br>

<a href="http://sln.fi.edu/inquirer/diabetes.html">http://sln.fi.edu/inquirer/diabetes.html</a>

<p>

<li>&quot;Energy Balance and Obesity in Noninsulin-Dependent Diabetes&quot; by Leslie P. Kozak, PhD, is a 

technical article available on line. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.jax.org/research/documents/sci93/kozak.html">http://www.jax.org/research/documents/sci93/kozak.html</a>

<p>

<li><a href = "mailto:nvoron@voicenet.com">Neal R. Voron</a>, president of the 

Night Shift Initiative, has republished an article by 

Dr. David S.H. Bell called &quot;The Graveyard Shift,&quot; which 

originally appeared in the February 1994 issue of <i>Diabetes Forecast</i> magazine and was written

 specifically for an audience of people with diabetes.

The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.nightshift.com/diabetes1/ada.html">http://www.nightshift.com/diabetes1/ada.html</a>

<p>

<li> &quot;Focus On... Diabetes Mellitus&quot; is an article by Lynn Wilson reprinted from the 

<i>Medical Sciences Bulletin</i> by Pharmaceutical Information Associates Ltd.  The

article discusses IDDM and NIDDM and the 

drugs used in the treatment of NIDDM. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.pharminfo.com/pubs/msb/diabetes.html">http://www.pharminfo.com/pubs/msb/diabetes.html</a>

<p>

<li> Access Excellence is a national educational program sponsored by Genentech Inc. that puts 

high school biology teachers in touch with their colleagues, scientists, and critical sources of new 

scientific information through an on-line network. Search for terms of interest like 

&quot;diabetes&quot; and &quot;insulin&quot; to find dozens of well-written articles 

(note: search for each search term in a separate search since linking terms with &quot;or&quot; 

strangely returns fewer, not more, hits than searching for these terms separately). The URL is<br>

<a href="http://outcast.gene.com/ae/">http://outcast.gene.com/ae/</a>

<p>

<li> &quot;Seaweed fight diabetes and thicken cat food&quot;  by Atle Kjrvik, is an article about 

the first human transplant of an artificial pancreas. The surgery was carried

out by Dr. Patrick Soon-Shiong of St. Vincent Medical Center in Los Angeles, on May 6, 1993, on 

Steven Craig. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.oslo.sintef.no/gemini/1993-dec/48.html">http://www.oslo.sintef.no/gemini/1993-dec/48.html</a>

<p>

<li> &quot;Hyperglycemic Hyperosmolar Nonketotic Syndrome: How to recognize and manage this 

diabetic emergency&quot; is an on-line article by Theresa O'Hanlon-Nichols. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.ajn.org/ajn/1996/6.3/a603038e.1t">http://www.ajn.org/ajn/1996/6.3/a603038e.1t</a>

<p>

<li> &quot;MedicineNet POWER POINTS about DIABETES MELLITUS&quot; is a good basic 

article about diabetes. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.medicinenet.com/mainmenu/encyclop/ARTICLE/Art_D/diabet.htm">http://www.medicinenet.com/mainmenu/encyclop/ARTICLE/Art_D/diabet.htm</a>

<p>

<li>&quot;The Healing Handbook for Persons with Diabetes,&quot; developed by a diabetes 

educator and two physicians at the University of Massachusetts Medical Center in Worcester, 

Massachusetts, is available on-line at no cost. Spiral bound copies of the handbook can also be purchased for 

$14.95 per copy plus $5.00 for shipping. The URL is<br>

<a href="http://www.ummed.edu:8000/dept/diabetes/handbook/title_pg.htm">http://www.ummed.edu:8000/dept/diabetes/handbook/title_pg.htm</a>

<p>


</ol>
<p>
<HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=center SIZE=2 NOSHADE>
