<title>Diabetes Monitor - JDF - Kansas City Chapter
</TITLE></HEAD>
<body BGCOLOR="#DFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" ALINK="#0000FF" background="bd2.gif" VLINK="#FF0000">
<blockquote><P>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="jdf-logo.gif" ALT=" (JDF) " Height=101 Width=189 ALIGN="bottom">
<br>
<a href="http://www.jdfcure.com/">
<h1><strong>
<FONT SIZE="+5">J</FONT>uvenile <FONT SIZE="+5">D</FONT>iabetes <FONT SIZE="+5">F</FONT>oundation</a>
</strong></h1>
<h2>
<em><FONT SIZE="+3">T</FONT>he <FONT SIZE="+3">K</FONT>ansas <FONT SIZE="+3">C</FONT>ity <FONT SIZE="+3">C</FONT>hapter</em>
</H2>
<HR width=10%  size=1 noshade align=center>
</CENTER>
<P>
<STRONG>T</STRONG>he <STRONG><FONT SIZE="+2"> J</font>uvenile <FONT SIZE="+2"> D</font>iabetes <FONT SIZE="+2"> F</font>oundation</a>
&#151; <em>The Kansas City Chapter</em></STRONG> is dedicated
to the goal of its international headquarters in New York City:
fundraising for biomedical research to find a cure for diabetes mellitus and its complications.
<P>
<STRONG>T</STRONG>he Kansas City Chapter was originally organized in 1979;
it opened its office in Shawnee Mission, Kansas on September 20, 1994.
Our Chapter has recently expanded its Board of Directors to reflect the
diversity and dynamics of the Kansas City metropolitan area.
Future plans are to expand the JDF - Kansas City Chapter in the state
of Kansas and western Missouri.
<P>
<STRONG>C</STRONG>orporate participation in the annual <EM>Walk For The Cure</EM> is an
essential element of JDF's success, as are a major gift-giving
campaign, The $200 Million Capital campaign, and JDF's ongoing
Government Relations program with the Congress
and key governmental decision-makers.
In 1996, JDF contributed over
$31.3 million to research and research-related programs.
<p>
<STRONG>T</STRONG>he Second Annual Celebrity Monopoly Tournament and Gala,
which was held on May 11, 1996, raised net proceeds of $57,000 for diabetes.
Phil Witt, of WDAF-TV, was the emcee. TV commentators Kelly Waldo and Mike Walter from WDAF-TV and
Valissa Smith and Bob Thill of KCTV-5,
vied for bragging rights while playing on an outsized Monopoly board,
while fifty-one teams of
dinner guests competed at tournament tables.
<P>
<STRONG>O</STRONG>n September 21, 1996, the Kansas City Chapter held its second annual <EM>Walk For The Cure</EM> at Shawnee Mission Park, in Shawnee, Kansas.
Over 1100 Walkers participated, representing 57 corporations and other organizations.
They raised over $150,000 for research to cure diabetes.
<p>
<STRONG>T</STRONG>he <STRONG><FONT SIZE="+2"> J</font>uvenile <FONT SIZE="+2"> D</font>iabetes <FONT SIZE="+2"> F</font>oundation
&#151; <em>The Kansas City Chapter</em></STRONG> publishes a quarterly newsletter, <STRONG><FONT SIZE="+2"> JDF D</font>iscoveries</STRONG>.
<P>
<STRONG>T</STRONG>he <STRONG><FONT SIZE="+2"> J</font>uvenile <FONT SIZE="+2"> D</font>iabetes <FONT SIZE="+2"> F</font>oundation
&#151; <em>The Kansas City Chapter</em></STRONG>
now cosponsors an
<EM>Adult Type I Support Group</EM>.
On the second Monday of each month, you can join JDF and Saint Joseph Health Center
at 7 PM in the Community Center for Health Education
to address contemporary health issues, engage in active lifestyles, and manage one's diabetes.
<P>
<STRONG>F</STRONG>uture Chapter events include:
<ul>
<P>
<LI><STRONG>F</STRONG>ebruary 10, 1997: 
<em><a href="support.htm#JDFDSGSJHC">Adult Type I Support Group</a></EM> at Saint Joseph Health Center
<P>
<LI><STRONG>M</STRONG>arch 10, 1997:
<em><a href="support.htm#JDFDSGSJHC">Adult Type I Support Group</a></EM> at Saint Joseph Health Center
<P>
<LI><STRONG>A</STRONG>pril 5, 1997: <em>
David Koller Bullhead Fishing Classic,</em> benefitting JDF-KCC
(at Moundridge, KS)
<P>
<LI><STRONG>A</STRONG>pril 26, 1997: <em>Third Annual Celebrity Monopoly Tournament and Gala</em>
(at the Ritz-Carlton Hotel, Kansas City, MO)
<P>
</ul>
<HR width=20%  size=1 noshade align=center><P><CENTER>
<IMG SRC="jdf-smll.gif" Height=45 Width=84 ALT=" (JDF, KC Chapter) " ALIGN="bottom">
