<!--DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC
techie.htm
New Apr2,96
William W. Quick, MD
A proud product of zYf Productions
This file is safe for children. We endorse the SafeSurf concept-->
<HTML><HEAD>
<META http-equiv="PICS-Label" content='(PICS-1.0
"http://www.classify.org/safesurf/" l gen t for
"http://www.mdcc.com" r (SS~~000 1 SS~~100 1))'>
<title>Diabetes Monitor - Techie Stuff</TITLE></HEAD>
<body BGCOLOR="#DFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" ALINK="#0000FF" background="bd2.gif" VLINK="#FF0000">
<a name="top"></a><a name="_top"></a>
<table>
<td>
<IMG src="spinstar.gif" height=47 width=47 ALT=" " align=left>
</td><td>
<h2><strong>
<font SIZE="+3"><A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font>
<br>
<FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">Technical Stuff for <nobr>Very Curious Websurfers</nobr>
</FONT>
</td><br>
</table>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" width=100% Height=2 ALT=" ">
</h2></strong>
<blockquote><P>
<font color="#ff00cc">
 . . . as of December 28, 1996
</font><P>

<IMG SRC="greendot.gif" alt=" "  Height=14 Width=14>
There is a <em><a href="sitemap.htm">Site Map</a></em> of the
<FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>D</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font> <nobr><FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>M</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font>,</nobr>
which includes the complete URL of every webpage. 
<P>
<IMG SRC="greendot.gif" ALT=" "  Height=14 Width=14>
Informational hyperlinks
at the
<FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>D</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font> <FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>M</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font>
are marked with

<blockquote><p>
the MDCC logo
<IMG SRC="mdcc1414.gif" alt=" " height=14 width=14>
(if at the
<FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>D</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font> <FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>M</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font>
</a></em>
<br>
or the cwD logo
<IMG SRC="cwd_1414.gif" alt=" " height=14 width=14>
(if at
<STRONG>
<b>children</b>
with
<b>DIABETES</b>)
</a></em>
<br>
or a star
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" "> (if on the Internet elsewhere)
<br>
or a red ball
<IMG SRC="reddot.gif" Height=14 Width=14 ALT=" unavailable ">
if unavailable.
</blockquote>

<IMG SRC="greendot.gif" alt=" "  Height=14 Width=14>
The
<FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>D</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font> <FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>M</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font>
has a hidden <a href="egg-info.htm"><em>Easter Egg</em></a>
for you to find!
<P>
<IMG SRC="greendot.gif" alt=" "  Height=14 Width=14>
<strong> Y</strong>ou can look at
the
<FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>D</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font> <FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>M</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR's</font>
<A HREF="stats/index.htm">
<em> Website Access Report,</em></A>
which is updated daily. Find out who else is learning from which pages at this website!
<P>
<IMG SRC="greendot.gif" alt=" "  Height=14 Width=14>
All of the webpages of
<FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>D</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font> <FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>M</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font>
include a pale blue background.

<blockquote><P>
If you don't see a pale blue background on this page,
and if your webbrowser supports background colors, you can change the settings.
<blockquote><P>
For Netscape Navigator&#153; version 1.2
go to <strong>&quot;Options&quot; &quot;Preferences...&quot; &quot;Colors&quot;</strong>
and change the setting to <strong>&quot;Use Colors From: Document, if Present.&quot;</strong>
<P>
For Netscape Navigator&#153; version 2.x
go to <strong>&quot;Options&quot; &quot;General Preferences...&quot; &quot;Colors&quot;</strong>
and unmark the box <strong>&quot;Always Use My Colors, Overriding Document.&quot;</strong>
(NOTE: You may have a beta version of version 2 that might require you click and unclick this box several
times to finally get the blue color.)
<P>
Your monitor must also be set to display at least 256 colors.
</blockquote>
</blockquote>
<IMG SRC="greendot.gif" alt=" "  Height=14 Width=14>
For websurfers with Netscape Navigator&#153; Version 2.x, or other advanced browsers,
the
<FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>D</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font> <FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>M</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font>
includes graphics files with movement. (Users of other webbrowsers will see
these files as graphics that are stationary.) Look at the red ball below
to see if your webbrowser is able to display movement in these graphics:
<center>
<br><IMG SRC="moveball.gif" align="middle">
</center>
<P>
<IMG SRC="greendot.gif" alt=" "  Height=14 Width=14>
For websurfers with Netscape Navigator&#153; Version 2.x, or other advanced browsers,
the
<FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>D</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font> <FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>M</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font>
includes the option to use index frames <strong>on the right side of the screen.</strong>
</blockquote>

<blockquote><p>
<blockquote><p>
The use of frames will be activated whenever you
go to the <strong>bottom of Page One,</strong>our home page, and click on the
&quot;Table of Contents&quot; hyperlink, or
click on the letter
<FONT SIZE="+2"><a href="with.htm">&quot;M&quot;</a></FONT> in
<FONT SIZE="+2"> D</FONT>IABETES <FONT SIZE="+2"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT>ONITOR<FONT SIZE="+1">&#153;</FONT>
at the <strong>top of any page.</strong> (You could think of the letter
<FONT SIZE="+2"> <A HREF="with.htm" TARGET="top">
&quot;M&quot;</a></FONT>
in the word Fra<FONT SIZE="+2"><A HREF="with.htm" TARGET="top">M</a></FONT>es.)
<P>
To view without frames, click on
&quot;View Without Frames&quot;
at the bottom of the Table of Contents in the right-side frame,
or click on the letter <FONT SIZE="+2"><a href="index.htm">&quot;D&quot;</a></FONT> in
<FONT SIZE="+2"> <a href="index.htm" TARGET="_top">
D</a></FONT>IABETES <FONT SIZE="+2">M</FONT>ONITOR<FONT SIZE="+1">&#153;</FONT>
at the top of any page. (Think of
<FONT SIZE="+2"> <a href="index.htm" TARGET="_top">
&quot;D&quot;</a></FONT>
as meaning,<FONT SIZE="+2"> <a href="index.htm" TARGET="_top">
D</a></FONT>on't use frames.)
<P>
The index frame will be more useful if you resize your webbrowser to <strong>Maximize</strong>,
or if you set the size to occupy the full vertical dimension, and at least one-half of the horizontal width, of your monitor's viewing area.
</blockquote>

<h2><IMG SRC="greendot.gif" alt=" " height=15 width=14>
What you won&#0146;t find at the
<STRONG>
<font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">D</font><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">M</font><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font></STRONG>
</h2>

<blockquote><P>
We&#0146;d had requests for more information about some website features that we&#0146;re
<strong>not</strong> currently implementing. The following are available on the internet,
at the 
<IMG SRC="cwd_1414.gif" alt=" " height=14 width=14>
<STRONG><em><a href="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/">
children
with DIABETES
</a></em></strong>
website, but not at the
<strong><font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">D</font><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<font size="+2" color="#ff00cc">M</font><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font></STRONG>
website:
<blockquote><P>
<em><IMG SRC="cwd_1414.gif" alt=" " height=14 width=14>
<a href="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/d_0l_000.htm">
Chat rooms about diabetes,</a>

<br><IMG SRC="cwd_1414.gif" alt=" " height=14 width=14>
<a href="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/d_0f_000.htm">
Bulletin Boards or Message Boards about diabetes,</a>

<br><IMG SRC="cwd_1414.gif" alt=" " height=14 width=14>
<a href="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/d_06_100.htm">
Meter information and reviews,</a></em> and
<em>
<br><IMG SRC="cwd_1414.gif" alt=" " height=14 width=14>
<a href="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/d_0d_000.htm">
Questions and answers from readers about diabetes.</a>
</em>
</blockquote>
The following are not really anticipated at any time in the foreseeable future:
<ul>
<li>Huge pictures that take forever to load,
<li>Sound, or
<li>Movies or movie clips.
</ul>
</blockquote>
</blockquote>

