<TITLE>Dr. Quick's Curriculum Vitae</TITLE></HEAD>
<body BGCOLOR="#DFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" ALINK="#0000FF" background="bd2.gif" VLINK="#FF0000">
<a name="top"></a><a name="_top"></a>
<table>
<td>
<IMG src="spinstar.gif" height=47 width=47 ALT=" " align=left>
</td><td>
<h2><strong>
<font SIZE="+3"><A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font>
<br>
<FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">Curriculum Vitae</font>
<br>William W. Quick, MD, FACP, FACE, CDE</FONT>
</td><br>
</table>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" width=100% Height=2 ALT=" ">
</h2></strong>
<blockquote><P>
<font color="#ff00cc">
 . . . as of January 27, 1997
</font>
<P><hr>
<H2>PERSONAL:</H2>
<blockquote><P>
Born: April 7, 1943, Portsmouth, NH
<br>Married: Stephanie Schwartz, RN, MPH, CDE
<br>Residence: Kansas City, Missouri
<br>Website:  <a href="http://www.kanddu.com">Katz & Dawgs Unlimited</a>
(<em><a href="http://www.kanddu.com">http://www.kanddu.com</a></em>)
<br>Employment<a href="cv-wwq-p.htm">:</a> Medical Director, Midwest Diabetes Care Center, Inc.
1515 West Truman Road, Suite 504, Independence, MO 64050
<br>E-mail: <em><A HREF="mailto:wquick@mdcc.com">wquick@mdcc.com</A></em>
</blockquote><P><hr>
<H2>EDUCATION:</H2>
<blockquote><P>
BA: College of Wooster, Wooster, Ohio, 1964.
<br>MD: State University of NY, Downstate Medical Center, 1968.
<br>Internship &amp; Residency, Internal Medicine:  University of MO Medical
Center, <nobr>1968 &#151; 1971.</nobr>
<br>Fellowship, Endocrinology: University of MO Medical Center,
<nobr>1971 &#151; 1972.</nobr>
</blockquote><P><hr>
<H2>CERTIFICATION &amp; LICENSURE:</H2>
<blockquote><P>
Certified by American Board of Internal Medicine, 1974.
<br>Certified by American Board of Internal Medicine, Subspecialty Board on
Endocrinology, Diabetes and Metabolism, 1977.
<br>Fellow, American College of Physicians, 1977.
<br>Fellow, American College of Endocrinology, 1994.
<br>Certified Diabetes Educator, National Certification Board for Diabetes
Educators, 1986; <nobr>recertified, 1992.</nobr>
<P>Licensed to practice medicine in Iowa (<I>inactive</I>), Kansas (<I>inactive</I>), Missouri, Nebraska, and South Dakota.
</blockquote><P><hr>
<H2>HOSPITAL and other APPOINTMENTS:</H2>
<blockquote><P>
Active Staff at 
Columbia-Independence
Regional Health Center (Independence, MO),
Medical Center of Independence (Independence, MO), 
Saint Mary&#0146;s Hospital (Blue Springs, MO).
<P>
Medical Officer, State Board of Registration for the Healing Arts,
1997 &#151; present.</nobr>
</blockquote><P><hr>
<H2>PROFESSIONAL INTERESTS:</H2>
<blockquote><P>
<H3>Diabetes Education and Diabetes Care</H3>
American Association of Diabetes Educators: Board of Directors (1979-86); Treasurer, Vice President, President-Elect, President (1985 &#151; 1986).
<br>American Diabetes Association: President, SD Affiliate, <nobr>1974 &#151; 1975.</nobr>
Kansas City Chapter of MO Affiliate: <nobr>Board of Directors, 1987 to 1994.</nobr> Served on
several state committees of MO Affiliate. Representative to Central Council of
ADA, 1985 &#151; 1991. Eastern Jackson County Chapter of MO Affiliate: Board of
Directors, <nobr>1995 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>Missouri Department of Health Bureau of High Risk Intervention, Diabetes
Advisory Committee:  <nobr>Co-chair, 1991 &#151; 1994;</nobr> <nobr>Chair, 1994 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>Santa Claus at Children&#0146;s Diabetes Center Christmas Party (Children&#0146;s Mercy
Hospital, Kansas City, MO), <nobr>1993 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>Reviewer for diabetes articles, <em>The Medical Letter&#174; On Drugs and Therapeutics</em>, <nobr>1993 &#151; present.</nobr>

<H3>Medical Education</H3>
Associate Professor of Internal Medicine and Psychiatry, University of SD,
<nobr>1978 &#151; 1985.</nobr>
<br>Lecturer and Preceptor, Goppert Family Practice Residency, Kansas City, <nobr>1987
&#151; 1994.</nobr>
<br>Lecturer and Preceptor, University of Health Sciences, Kansas City, <nobr>1988 &#151;
1992.</nobr>
<br>Lecturer on Endocrinology, Critical Care RN Review Courses, at Baptist
Medical Center, and at Saint Joseph Health Center, <nobr>1988 &#151; 1993.</nobr>
<br>Lecturer, Bess Truman Family Practice Residency, Kansas City,
<nobr>1996 &#151; present.</nobr>
<p>Numerous lectures on diabetes and endocrinology topics for
American Diabetes Association and Juvenile Diabetes Foundation Chapters,
local diabetes support groups,
and professional education meetings.

<H3>Medical Applications of Computers</H3>
Member, Medical Informatics Committee, Columbia-Independence
Regional Health Center, 1993 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>Beta tester, health-related and other software: DesignWorks (1993); MedCoach (1995); Stedman&#0146;s Medical Dictionary (1996).
<p>Author of website, <A HREF="http://www.mdcc.com">
<FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>D</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font> <FONT SIZE="+1" color="#FF0000"><STRONG>M</STRONG></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR</font></A>
(at <em><A HREF="http://www.mdcc.com">
http://www.mdcc.com</a></em>), <nobr>1995 &#151; present.</nobr>
<blockquote><P>
&#0147;The Diabetes Monitor of the Midwest Diabetes Care Center keeps getting better and better. One of the most valuable Web sites for diabetics, the Diabetes Monitor is also one of the most
comprehensive and best designed. Dr. William W. Quick, a specialist in diabetes care and endocrinology, heads the Midwest Diabetes Care Center in Independence, Missouri, near Kansas City.&#0148;
(Rick Mendosa, reviewer; in 
<a href="http://www.cruzio.com/~mendosa/faq.html">
On-line Resources for Diabetics</a>)

<P>
&#0147;Diabetes Monitor claims to track every diabetes site in cyberspace. A tall order, but
as far as we can tell, it fulfills its mission admirably. Diabetes Monitor is a must visit
for anyone with questions about diabetes--any questions. Constructed by the
Midwest Diabetes Care Center of Independence, Missouri, this site contains a truly
vast number of articles and links.&#0148;
(<a href="http://www.diabetes.com/site/MISC/SRBODY.HTM?ID=33">Diabetes.com Site Reviews</a>)

</blockquote>
Author of webpage for
<a href="jdf-kcc.htm">
Kansas City Chapter of the JDF</a>
(at <em><a href="jdf-kcc.htm">
http://www.mdcc.com/jdf-kcc.htm</a></em>), <nobr>1995 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>Educational Sharing Session: Diabetes on the Internet; American Association of Diabetes Educators Annual Meeting, <nobr>August, 1995.</nobr>
<br>Medical Director of website,
<a href="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/">
<b>children</b> with <B>DIABETES</b></a>
(at <em><a href="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/">http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/</a></em>),
<nobr>1995 &#151; present.</nobr>

<H3>Recent Publications</H3>
<I>The Other Tests Your Doctor Orders. </I>Diabetes in the News, August,
1988.
<br><I>Pathophysiology of Diabetes.</I> In Diabetes Education: A Core
Curriculum for Health Professionals, American Association of Diabetes Educators, 1988.
<br><I>Pathophysiology of Diabetes.</I> In Diabetes Education: A Core
Curriculum for Health Professionals, American Association of Diabetes Educators, Second Edition, 1993.

<H3>Professional Organizations</H3>
American Association of Clinical Endocrinologists, Charter Member, <nobr>1991 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>American Association of Diabetes Educators, <nobr>1979 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>American College of Endocrinology, <nobr>1994 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>American College of Physicians, <nobr>1972 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>American Diabetes Association, <nobr>1972 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>American Medical Association. <nobr>1996 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>Endocrine Society, <nobr>1973 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>Kansas City Round Table of Endocrinology, <nobr>1994 &#151; present.</nobr>
<br>Metropolitan Medical Society of Greater Kansas City, 1987 &#151; present.</nobr> Member of the Board of
Directors, <nobr>1995 &#151; present.</nobr>
</blockquote></blockquote>

</blockquote>
