<h2><strong>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=100% ALT=" "><br>
<IMG SRC="mdcc2222.gif" ALT=" " height=22 width=22>
<font SIZE="+4"> <A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">
D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+4"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3"> NIH F</FONT>unding <FONT SIZE="+3">U</FONT>pdate 
<BR><IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=100% ALT=" "></H2>
</h1></center><BLOCKQUOTE><center></strong></H1>
<p>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
</center><blockquote><P><blockquote><P>
<center><h2>
<IMG SRC="jdf-smll.gif" Height=45 Width=84 ALT=" (JDF logo) ">
<br>
Government Relations Legislative Alert:
<nobr>Status of NIH Funding</nobr>
<nobr>(September 16, 1996)</nobr>
</h2></center></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote>
<p><center>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
</center><P>
On Thursday, September 12th, the Senate Appropriations Committee
approved its version of H.R. 3755, the Fiscal Year (FY) 1997 Labor, HHS
and Education Appropriations bill.  The result was a recommended increase
of approximately $487 million, or 4.1 percent, for the National
Institutes of Health (NIH) over last year's level, and an increase of
approximately $28.9 million, or 3.8 percent, for the National Institute
of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases (NIDDK).  Earlier this
summer, the House recommended an increase of $820 million, or 6.9
percent, for the NIH and an increase of $49 million, or 6.3 percent, for
NIDDK.
<P>
The bill is expected to be considered on the Senate Floor during the
week of September 16th.  However, due to the short amount of time before
Congress adjourns (expected around the end of September), we anticipate
that funding for the NIH and NIDDK will be contained in a Continuing
Resolution (C.R.).
<P>
As more information becomes available, we will keep you updated.  If you
have any questions or concerns, contact Eric Schutt
at the
Juvenile Diabetes Foundation,
at <em><a href="mailto:ESCHUTT@JDFGOV.USA.COM">ESCHUTT@JDFGOV.USA.COM</a></em>
or call 1-800-JDF-1VOTE.
</blockquote><br><IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=100% ALT=" "><p>
<center><em><a href="#top">Return to the beginning of this document</a></em><br>
