<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=100% ALT=" "><br>
<IMG SRC="mdcc2222.gif" ALT=" " height=22 width=22>
<font SIZE="+4"><A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+4"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3">JDF</FONT> <FONT SIZE="+3">G</FONT>overnment <FONT SIZE="+3">R</FONT>elations <FONT SIZE="+3">L</FONT>egislative <FONT SIZE="+3"> A</FONT>lert: <nobr>July 11, 1996</nobr>
<BR><IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=100% ALT=" "></H2>
</h1></center>




<center>
<p>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
</center>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P><blockquote><P><blockquote><P>
<center>
<h2>
<IMG SRC="jdf-smll.gif" Height=45 Width=84 ALT=" (JDF logo) " ALIGN="bottom">
<P>
Government Relations Legislative Alert:
<P>
CALL YOUR REPRESENTATIVE REGARDING NIH FUNDING
</h2>
</center>

</blockquote></blockquote></blockquote>
<p>
<center>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
</center>
<P>
<h3>
To all JDF Internet Advocates:
</h3>

The Labor, HHS, Education Appropriations bill, H.R. 3755, which includes 
funding for the National Institutes of Health(NIH) will be debated on the 
House floor today.  During this debate Congressman Bill Goodling is 
scheduled to propose an amendment which would transfer $291 million from 
funding for the NIH to special education programs.  While we understand the 
importance of funding for these programs, we feel the dollars should not 
come from NIH.
<h3>
WHAT YOU NEED TO DO!!!!!!!!
</h3>
You need to get as many people as possible and have them contact their 
Congressperson by phone as soon as possible (hopefully before 1:00 p.m. 
est.) and ask them to not vote for any amendment offered to H.R. 3755 which 
would transfer money from NIH.  ONLY CALL YOUR CONGRESSPERSON! IF YOU CALL A 
CONGRESSPERSON OTHER THAN THE ONE WHO REPRESENTS YOUR CONGRESSIONAL 
DISTRICT, THE MESSAGE WILL BE DISCREDITED!  If you are not sure who your 
Congressperson is please contact the JDF Government Relations Department at 
1-800-533-1868.  If you do not know the phone number for your 
Congressperson, they can be reached by calling the Capitol Switchboard at 
(202) 224-3121.  When the operator answers, ask to speak to your 
Congressperson.
<P>
If you have any questions or concerns contact  Eric Schutt
at <em><a href="mailto:ESCHUTT@JDFGOV.USA.COM">ESCHUTT@JDFGOV.USA.COM</a></em>
<P>
</blockquote><br><IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=100% ALT=" "><p>
