</TR></TABLE><h2><strong>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=100% ALT=" "><br>
<IMG SRC="mdcc2222.gif" ALT=" " height=22 width=22>
<font SIZE="+4"><A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+4"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3">JDF</FONT> <FONT SIZE="+3">G</FONT>overnment <FONT SIZE="+3">R</FONT>elations <FONT SIZE="+3">L</FONT>egislative <FONT SIZE="+3">A</FONT>lert: <nobr>April 1996</nobr>
<BR><IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=100% ALT=" "></H2>
</h1><center>

<p>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
</center>
<blockquote><P><blockquote><P><blockquote><P>
<h2>
<IMG SRC="jdf-smll.gif" Height=45 Width=84 ALT=" (JDF logo) ">
<P>
Government Relations Legislative Alert:
<P>
TOWN HALL MEETINGS
</h2>
</blockquote></blockquote></blockquote>
<p>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
</center>

<P>

Over the next six months, many U.S. Representatives, U.S. Senators, and
Presidential
candidates will be holding Town Hall Meetings or Campaign Candidate Debate
Forums in your area.  We feel it is critical for you to attend these events
and to speak out
about the importance of medical research funding, and more specifically
diabetes
research funding through the National Institutes of Health (NIH).  It is
your duty and
right, as a constituent, a taxpayer, and as someone who is deeply affected
by the benefits
of medical research, to tell these officials your priorities for federal
spending.
<P>
With this in mind, it is crucial that you call your legislators district
offices in your area
and ask them for the date, time, and place of the next Town Hall meeting.
 If none are
currently scheduled, ask to be put on the the Town Hall meeting invitation
mailing list.
To find out the dates for campaign candidate debates, you should call each
candidates
campaign headquarters and ask for a schedule of debates (these may not occur
until late
Summer or early Fall).
<P>
When you receive a date for a Town Hall meeting or candidates debate forum
in your
area, it is critical that you plan on attending.  It is also important that
you call the JDF
Government Relations Department in DC to let us know when and where these
meetings
will occur so that we can get the word out to other volunteers in your area.
<P>
The most important question to ask elected officials or candidates at these
forums is:
<blockquote><P>
&#0147;The
104th Congress made federally funded medical research through the NIH a
national
priority, if (re-)elected to the 105th Congress will you maintain federally
funded medical research through the NIH as a national priority by fighting and
working for
much needed increases?&#0148;
</blockquote>
If you have any questions, or need any additional information, please call
Bill Schmidt or
Eric Schutt in the JDF Government Relations Department at 1 (800) JDF-1VOTE
or send e-mail to <a href="mailto:ESCHUTT@JDFGOV.USA.COM"><em>ESCHUTT@JDFGOV.USA.COM</em></a>
</blockquote><br><IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=100% ALT=" "><p>
