<HTML><HEAD>
<META http-equiv="PICS-Label" content='(PICS-1.0
"http://www.classify.org/safesurf/" l gen t for
"http://www.mdcc.com" r (SS~~000 1 SS~~100 1))'>
<title>Diabetes Monitor - Times to check your Blood Sugar</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#DFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" ALINK="#0000ff" VLINK="#ff0000">
<a name="top"></a>



<CENTER><h2><strong>
<IMG SRC="mdcc2222.gif" Height=22 Width=22 ALT=" ">
<nobr><font SIZE="+3"><A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font></nobr>
<FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">
Times you might check your Blood Sugar
</FONT>
<BR><IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=100% ALT=" "></H2>
</h1></center>
<P><font color="#ff00cc">
 . . . as of April 9, 1996
</font><P>
<center><IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" "></center>
<blockquote><P><blockquote><P>
<center><h3>
Sometimes people wonder when it would be &#0147;best&#0148; to check the blood sugar level.
<P>
There isnt any single best time, but here are some of our suggestions:
</h3>
</center>
</blockquote></blockquote>
<p>
<center>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
</center>
<P>

<ul>
<li>Before meals.
<li>At bedtime.
<li>If you think you are having low sugar symptoms.
<li>If <strong>anyone</strong> thinks you are having low sugar symptoms.
<li>About one-and-a-half hours after eating.
<li>At about 3:00 AM.
<li>If you are ill. (Be sure to check several times daily; if the results are higher than usual, call for advice!)
<li>Before driving an automobile or operating other dangerous machinery.
<li>Both immediately before, and after, active exercise. (Also, if you have the chance, check an hour before the exercise).
<li>If you are curious.
</ul>
</blockquote>

<P><center>
<table width=95% bgcolor="#aaffff" border=2><td valign=middle align=center>
<table>
<td valign="middle" align="center">
<br>
