<title>Diabetes Monitor - Diabetes on the Web: Camps</TITLE>

<body BGCOLOR="#DFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" ALINK="#0000FF" background="bd2.gif" VLINK="#FF0000">
<a name="top"></a><a name="_top"></a>
<table>
<td>
<IMG src="spinstar.gif" height=47 width=47 ALT=" " align=left>
</td><td>
<h2><strong>
<font SIZE="+3"><A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font>
<br>
<FONT SIZE="+3" face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial"><STRONG>D</STRONG></FONT><FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">IABETES on the
<STRONG><FONT SIZE="+3">W</FONT></STRONG><FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">EB:
<br>Camps for People <nobr>with Diabetes</nobr></font>
</td><br>
</table>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" width=100% Height=2 ALT=" ">
</h2></strong>
<blockquote><P><font color="#ff00cc">
 . . . as of October 4, 1996
</font>
<P>
<IMG SRC="cwd_1414.gif" alt=" " height=14 width=14>
<a href="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/d_07_100.htm">
<em>Camps for Children with Diabetes</em></a>
(&quot;http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/d_07_100.htm&quot;)
<br>
A comprehensive listing of diabetes camping experiences.
Some of the listed camps have their own websites (including those
listed below); others have information that is part of the <b>
children with DIABETES</b> website.
<br>
<img src="mdcc1414.gif"  Alt=" " height=14 width=14>
<a href="camp.htm">
<em>
Diabetes Camps for Youth in Missouri
</em></a>
(&quot;http://www.mdcc.com/camp.htm&quot;)
<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<a name="C96E"></a>
<a href="http://www.angel.co.uk/srcs/bda_web.html">
<em>Calshot 96 Experience</em></a>
(&quot;http://www.angel.co.uk/srcs/bda_web.html&quot;)
<br>
A holiday for diabetic adolescents run by the British Diabetic Association.
<a name="chh"></a>
<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<a href="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/d_07_240.htm">
<em>Camp Hickory Hill</em></a>
(&quot;http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/d_07_240.htm&quot;)
<br>Camp Hickory Hill is a summer residence camp in Columbia, Missouri, for children with diabetes ages 8 through 17.
<br>
<a name="sweeney"></a>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<a href="http://www.campsweeney.org">
<em>Camp Sweeney</em></a>
(&quot;http://www.campsweeney.org&quot;)
<br>&#147;Camp Sweeney is a non-profit organization that has operated  each summer
since 1950 with the purpose of teaching a lifestyle to children with
diabetes in order to have them live longer healthier lives. We serve
approximately 650 children between the ages of six to eighteen in a ten
week period each summer.
Camp Sweeney is pleased in announce that it is offering several services
on the INTERNET. These areas can be accessed by anyone with access to
the INTERNET. There are no additional charges for these services other
that what you pay for your access from your provider.
Our Web area offers our on-line brochure and application, latest
information on upcoming camp programs, and live chat support areas for
children with diabetes. The latter of these services offers an
innovative live forum in which children with diabetes can communicate
with each other from anywhere on the globe 24 hours a day. In addition
every Thursday night at 8:00 PM CST we  feature a live one-hour session
with one of our camp counselors.  It is our intent and  hope that this
live forum will provide  support and fellowship for children with
diabetes throughout the world.&#148;
<a name="campmag"></a>
<br>
<IMG SRC="new3.gif" ALT=" New! ">
<IMG SRC="star.gif" height=14 width=14 alt=" ">
<a href="http://www.castlepoint.com/wwcamp/campman/article4.html">
<em>
Understanding Your Camper with Diabetes - It's more than shots and sugar
</em></a>
(&quot;http://www.castlepoint.com/wwcamp/campman/article4.html&quot;)
<br>
From
<a href="http://www.castlepoint.com/wwcamp/campman/campman.html">
<em>
Camp Management
</em></a>
&#147;The only independent magazine dedicated to helping children's camp owners and directors run successful camps.&#148;
<a name="mokan"></a>
<P>
<h3>
<IMG SRC="Greendot.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
Dates for 1996 Kansas diabetes camps (not available on the web):</h3>
<blockquote><P>
June 23-29) Camp Discovery 1996: Session I (Rock Springs Ranch, Junction City, KS). For kids who have completed
grades 6, 7, or 8. Call ADA, Kansas Affiliate, at 1-800-362-1355.
<br>
June 30 - July 5) Camp Discovery 1996: Session II (Rock Springs Ranch, Junction City, KS). For teens who have
completed grades 9, 10, 11, or 12. Call ADA, Kansas Affiliate, at 1-800-362-1355
<br>
July 6-10) Camp Discovery 1996: Session III (Rock Springs Ranch, Junction City, KS). For kids who have completed
 grades 3, 4, or 5. Call ADA, Kansas Affiliate, at 1-800-362-1355.
</blockquote>


