<em>The Discovery of Insulin
</em></a>
&quot;http://qlink.queensu.ca/~3jdb3/contents.htm&quot;
<br>
&#0147;On July 30th 1921, Dr. Frederick Banting and Charles Best, while working alone in a hot stuffy laboratory at the University of Toronto, got the first positive response from their new extract tested on a diabetic dog --- the birth of insulin. This web page is dedicated to The Discovery of Insulin, one of the most
significant medical discoveries of this century. This web site is dedicated to the 75th Anniversary of The Discovery of
Insulin.  It features information about the discovery that has previously not
been available for public viewing: including transcribed newspaper
articles from 1920&#0146;s to the 1950&#0146;s, pictures of the discovery team, a
history of the homestead where Dr. Banting grew up in Alliston, Ont.
Also the site features the only known recording of Dr. Banting&#0146;s voice,
sending Christmas wishes to the troops overseas (~1941).&#0148;
<br>
By Jim Banting
