<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" width=100% Height=2 ALT=" ">
</h2></strong>
<blockquote><P>
<P><font color="#ff00cc">
 . . . as of November 23, 1996
</font></blockquote>

<center>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" height=2 width=50% alt=" ">
<P>
<h2>Diabetes Care Programs<br>
Recognized by the American Diabetes Association</h2>
<IMG SRC="adalogo.gif" ALT=" ADA logo " ALIGN="bottom"></center>

<blockquote><P>
<blockquote><P>
&#147;Recognition&#148; is a voluntary process
that formally identifies
diabetes patient education programs that meet the <B>National
Standards for Diabetes Patient Education</B> as developed and
tested under the auspices of the National Diabetes Advisory Board.
<P>
As of September 26, 1996,
481 programs from 48 states and the District of Columbia have been &#0147;Recognized.&#0148;
<p>
</blockquote>
</blockquote>

<a name="listing"></a>
<center>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" height=2 width=50% alt=" ">
</center>
<center>
<h3>
 The following Recognized Programs are located
in Kansas and Missouri
<br>(arranged alphabetically
by city):
</h3>
