<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<A HREF="http://pages.prodigy.com/CA/nutrigenie">
<em>
Nutrigenie</A>
</EM></A>
(&#0147;http://pages.prodigy.com/CA/nutrigenie&#0148;)
<br>
Nutrigenie
is a nutrition software publisher. Their mission is &#0147;to create
quality software for better health.&#0148; Several products would be interesting
for people with diabetes
to review; and you can download evaluation copies.
<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<A HREF="http://www.dmi.net/pjfudge/">
<em>P.J. Fudge and Chocolate Company
</EM></A>
(&#0147;http://www.dmi.net/pjfudge/&#0148;)
<br>
P.J. Fudge and Chocolate Company makes sugar free fudge and chocolate products.
Their website include dietary information,
and you can order by e-mail.
<a name="DD"></a>
<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<A HREF="http://www.ewalker.com/dd/dd.htm">
<em>Diabetic Delights</em>
</A>
(&#0147;http://www.ewalker.com/dd/dd.htm&#0148;)
<br>
An electronic bakery
that &#0147;allows you to browse and purchase all types of diabetic desserts.
We have complied a multitude of dessert products that are suited to the
special dietary needs of diabetics and others with special dietary
requirements.&#0148;
<br>
<img src="mdcc1414.gif"  Alt=" " height=14 width=14>
<A HREF="olestra.htm">
<em>Olestra</em></A>
(&#0147;http://www.mdcc.com/olestra.htm&#0148;)
<br>
A synthetic fat product that is now available in the U.S.
<a name="joannel"></a>
<br>
<IMG SRC="moved.gif" Height=18 Width=51 ALT=" Moved! ">
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<a href="http://www.http://www.dietitian.com">
<em>Ask the Dietitian
</em></A>
(&#0147;http://www.http://www.dietitian.com&#0148;)
<br>
Includes Q&A's about diabetes and meal planning.
<br>
By Joanne Larsen, MS, RD
[Moved to new URL in December, 1996]
<a name="glyind"></a>
<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<a href="http://www.cruzio.com/~mendosa/gi.html"><em>Glycemic Index</em></a>
(&#0147;http://www.cruzio.com/~mendosa/gi.html&#0148;)
<br>Discussion about the Glycemic Index:
&#0147;The GI shows how quickly
different foods make glucose available, something of great importance to diabetics.&#0148;
<br>
By Tere Griffin and Rick Mendosa
<a name="sugar"></a>
<br><IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<em>
<a href="http://ificinfo.health.org/sugar.htm">
What You Should Know About Sugars
</a></em>
(&#0147;http://ificinfo.health.org/sugar.htm&#0148;)
<br>With references to the scientific literature.
<br>From the &#0147;International Food Information Council Foundation's World Wide Web Server, the source on
food-related issues.&#0148;
<a name="960818a"></a>
<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/Sweet_Health">
Sweet Health</a></em>
(&#0147;http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/Sweet_Health&#0148;)
<br>
&#0147;Sweet Health provides an on-line catalog of gourmet sugar-free
food that is intended for diabetic adults and children, as
well as all concerned with their sugar intake.
Full nutritional information per FDA labels is provided
for every product. Much research has been performed to
establish the safety and quality of these foods. Part of
proceeds go towards diabetic education and research.&#0148;
<a name="nhv"></a>
<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://www.nhv.com/nhv">
National Health Video, Inc.</a></em>
(&#0147;http://www.nhv.com/nhv&#0148;)
<br>
National Health Video is a company specializing in consumer education.
Their site includes Diet Tips, Diet Quiz, Diabetes Tips;
NHV has Books, Software, and Videos for sale
<a name="besfc"></a>
<br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://www.sugar-free.com">
Bonnie Ellen's Sugar-Free Candies</a></em>
(&#0147;http://www.sugar-free.com&#0148;)
<a name="fandd"></a><br>
<IMG SRC="cwd_1414.gif" alt=" " height=14 width=14>
<em><a href="http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/d_08_000.htm">
Food and Diet</a></em>
(&#0147;http://www.castleweb.com/diabetes/d_08_000.htm&#0148;)
From <b>children with DIABETES</b>
<a name="thedg"></a><br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://www.norwich.net/gourmet/ezine/diabetic/dgdishes.htm">
The Diabetic Gourmet
</a></em>
(&#0147;http://www.norwich.net/gourmet/ezine/diabetic/dgdishes.htm&#0148;)
&#0147;Diabetics can enjoy delicious meals! Our
monthly menu includes a great selection of
dishes for you to try out. All recipes include
nutritional info and exchanges... the Diabetic
Gourmet can enjoy really great food.
Bon Appetit!&#0148;
<a name="rcptoday"></a><br>
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://www.diabetes.org/ada/rcptoday.html">
Recipe of the day</a></em>
(&#0147;http://www.diabetes.org/ada/rcptoday.html&#0148;)
&#0147;Featuring a new healthy
recipe every day, Monday through Friday.&#0148;
From the American Diabetes Association

<a name="fastf"></a><br>
<IMG SRC="new3.gif" ALT=" New! ">
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://www.olen.com/food/">Food Finder</a></em>
(&#0147;http://www.olen.com/food/&#0148;)
Based on the book Fast Food Facts by the Minnesota Attorney General's Office.
The search button says &#0147;Fire up the deep fryer&#0148;!
<br>
<a name="infoas"></a>
<IMG SRC="new3.gif" ALT=" New! ">
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://alpha.rollanet.org/library/SugarSumm.html">
Information about Sugars
</a></em>
(&#0147;http://alpha.rollanet.org/library/SugarSumm.html&#0148;)
Gives nice succinct definitions, telling what each name really is. An example:
<blockquote>
Glucose / dextrose / "blood sugar" / corn sugar:
Glucose is a monosaccharide. This simple sugar is derivable from converted starches such as what happens when
mashing malted grain. Sugar processors can make this sugar from a variety of sources - corn (maize), wheat, rice,
potatoes, in short, anything with cheap starch can be a input into the process. However if not completely refined
down to simple sugars, some of the origin can be discerned. The "right handed" variation of glucose is called dextrose.
</blockquote>
by Bob Devine

<br>
<a name="zbar"></a>
<IMG SRC="new3.gif" ALT=" New! ">
<IMG SRC="star.gif" Height=14 Width=14 alt=" ">
<em><a href="http://www.zbar.com">Zbar</a></em>
(&#0147;http://www.zbar.com&#0148;)
&#0147;The great tasting, long acting carbohydrate snack that reduces the risk of hypoglycemic episodes.
Available from your local pharmacy in three great tasting flavors!&#0148;
From Baker Norton Pharmaceuticals, Inc.

