<HTML><HEAD>
<META http-equiv="PICS-Label" content='(PICS-1.0
"http://www.classify.org/safesurf/" l gen t for
"http://www.mdcc.com" r (SS~~000 1 SS~~100 1))'>
<title>Diabetes Monitor - Hypoglycemia</TITLE></HEAD>
<body BGCOLOR="#DFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" ALINK="#0000FF" background="bd2.gif" VLINK="#FF0000">
<a name="top"></a><a name="_top"></a>
<table>
<td>
<IMG src="spinstar.gif" height=47 width=47 ALT=" " align=left>
</td><td>
<h2><strong>
<font SIZE="+3"><A HREF="index.htm" TARGET="_top">D</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">IABETES</font>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><a href="with.htm" TARGET="_top">M</a></FONT><font color="#ff00cc">ONITOR:</font>
<br>
<FONT face="Rockwell, Comic Sans MS, Arial">
How to protect from Hypoglycemia</FONT>
</td><br>
</table>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" width=100% Height=2 ALT=" ">
</h2></strong>
<blockquote><P>
<font color="#ff00cc">
 . . . as of May 1, 1996
</font>
</blockquote>



<P>
<center>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
<h3>Hypoglycemia is one of the major risks of tight control programs.
<br>Here are some hints on dealing with it.
</h3><p>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=50% ALT=" ">
<P></center>
<BLOCKQUOTE><p>
<ul><li>Frequent blood sugar testing
<li>Eat (or cut your dose of insulin) before exercise
<li>Eat before driving (or check your sugar level)
<li>Test every hour when driving
<li>Let it run high in unusual circumstances
<li>Inform your friends and family and coworkers to feed your face if you are flaky
<LI>Test one hour before, immediately before, and after exercise
<LI>Drink juice or Gatorade if thirsty during prolonged exercise
<LI>be aware of the possibility of delayed reactions:Eat extra protein before bedtime if heavy exercise after noontime
<LI>File a flight plan before solo exercise
<LI>Dont use Regular insulin at bedtime (unless you tell someone else who will be there at 3am to help if you crash)
<LI>Wear MedicAlert ID (call 1-800-ID-ALERT for more information)
<LI>Leave your clunky old ID in the car (not in the bedroom dresser drawer!)
<LI>Be sure that your family knows how to give Glucagon shots (and make sure they know where its stored!)
<LI>Treat low numbers even if no symptoms
<li>Stash sugar:
<ul>
<LI>in your pockets
<LI>EVERY car you're likely to be in
<LI>purse
<li>suitcase
<li>briefcase
<li>with your meter
<LI>diaper bag
<LI>bedside
<LI>garage
<LI>basement
<LI>upstairs
<LI>attic
<LI>bathroom
<LI>next to your exercise machine
<LI>friends purses
<LI>boyfriend's or hubbys pockets
<li>your desk or locker at work
</ul></ul>

</blockquote>
<IMG SRC="red-line.gif" Height=2 Width=100% ALT=" ">
<P><center><em><a href="#top">Return to the beginning of this document</a></em></center>
<table width=99% cellspacing=0 cellpadding=3><td align=right valign=middle>
<FORM ACTION="/wsredir.isa" METHOD="GET">
